fastPathWLANSwitch.description: The Allied Telesis Private MIB for AT-UWC

WsOui.name: WsOui
WsOui.description: 24-bit Organizationally Unique Identifier. Information on OUIs can be found in IEEE 802-2001 [802-2001] Clause 9.

TspecSuppAC.name: TspecSuppAC
TspecSuppAC.description: Access category (AC) used for TSPEC. Only those ACs that support mandatory admission control are listed here.

wsMibVersion.name: wsMibVersion
wsMibVersion.description: The version number of this MIB module

wsMode.name: wsMode
wsMode.description: Flag to enable/disable wireless controller functionality on the device. Disable will purge all status and statistics related to wireless functionality.

wsCountryCode.name: wsCountryCode
wsCountryCode.description: This object indicates country of operation for WLAN. Supported country codes are: Australia - AU, Austria - AT, Austria - AT, Belgium - BE, Brazil - BR, Canada - CA, China - CN, Czech Republic - CZ, Denmark - DK, Finland - FI, France - FR, Germany - DE, Greece - GR, Hong Kong - HK, Hungary - HU, Iceland - IS, India - IN, Ireland - IE, Israel - IL, Italy - IT, Japan - JP, Liechtenstein - LI,Luxembourg - LU,Malaysia - MY, Mexico - MX, Netherlands - NL, New Zealand - NZ, Norway - NO, Poland - PL, Portugal - PT, Saudi Arabia - SA, Singapore - SG, Slovakia - SK, Slovenia - SI, South Africa - ZA, South Korea - KR, Spain - ES, Sweden - SE, Switzerland - CH, Taiwan - TW, Thailand - TH, United Arab Emirates - AE, United Kingdom - GB, United States - US.

wsPeerGroupId.name: wsPeerGroupId
wsPeerGroupId.description: This object indicates which peer group this controller belongs to, there may be more than one group of peer controllers in the WLAN.

wsAPValidationMethod.name: wsAPValidationMethod
wsAPValidationMethod.description: This object indicates whether or not to verify newly discovered APs and look up their configuration against the local database or a RADIUS server.

wsAPAuthenticationMode.name: wsAPAuthenticationMode
wsAPAuthenticationMode.description: Flag to indicate if authentication is required for an AP to establish communication with the controller.

wsClientRoamAgeTime.name: wsClientRoamAgeTime
wsClientRoamAgeTime.description: Time in seconds to wait after a client disassociates from a managed AP before deleting the client association database entry.

wsRFScanAgeTime.name: wsRFScanAgeTime
wsRFScanAgeTime.description: Time in hours to wait before deleting an entry obtained from an RF scan.A value of 0 in input range means that the entry never ages out.

wsAPFailureAgeTime.name: wsAPFailureAgeTime
wsAPFailureAgeTime.description: Time in hours to wait before deleting an entry in the AP association and authentication failure list. A value of 0 in input range means that the entry never ages out.

wsAdHocClientAgeTime.name: wsAdHocClientAgeTime
wsAdHocClientAgeTime.description: Time in hours to wait before deleting an entry in Ad hoc client list.A value of 0 in input range means that the entry never ages out.

wsDetectedClientAgeTime.name: wsDetectedClientAgeTime
wsDetectedClientAgeTime.description: Time in hours to wait before deleting an entry from the detected clients database.A value of 0 in input range means that the entry never ages out.

wsValidAPConfigTable.name: wsValidAPConfigTable
wsValidAPConfigTable.description: This table contains configurable parameters for a specific AP. When an AP is discovered and the wsValidationMethod is local, its MAC address is verified in this table to determine if it should be managed by the controller.

wsValidAPConfigEntry.name: wsValidAPConfigEntry
wsValidAPConfigEntry.description: Each entry has parameters that can be configured locally or on a RADIUS server, for a specific AP on the WLAN. As this table is indexed by wsAPMacAddress, - to create an entry, specify the AP MAC address and set object wsAPConfigRowStatus to createAndGo(4) - to delete an entry, select the entry from the list and set object wsAPConfigRowStatus to destroy(6)

wsAPLocation.name: wsAPLocation
wsAPLocation.description: This object indicates description of an AP, often based on its location.

wsAPMode.name: wsAPMode
wsAPMode.description: This field indicates whether this AP is managed by the controller, by an administrator, or is a Rogue AP.

wsAPAuthenticationPasswd.name: wsAPAuthenticationPasswd
wsAPAuthenticationPasswd.description: If AP authentication is enabled, this indicates the password for an AP to authenticate to the controller. This must match the password configured on an AP. When passwod is configured this object will always return '*****'.

wsUseAPProfileId.name: wsUseAPProfileId
wsUseAPProfileId.description: If AP is managed by controller, this object indicates Id of configuration profile for this AP.

wsAPRadio1Channel.name: wsAPRadio1Channel
wsAPRadio1Channel.description: This object indicates the fixed channel for the AP radio one. Zero indicates automatic channel assignment.

wsAPRadio2Channel.name: wsAPRadio2Channel
wsAPRadio2Channel.description: This object indicates the fixed channel for the AP radio two. Zero indicates automatic channel assignment.

wsAPRadio1TxPower.name: wsAPRadio1TxPower
wsAPRadio1TxPower.description: This indicates the power setting of AP radio one. Zero indicates automatic power adjustment.

wsAPRadio2TxPower.name: wsAPRadio2TxPower
wsAPRadio2TxPower.description: This indicates the power setting of AP radio two. Zero indicates automatic power adjustment.

wsAPStandaloneExpectedChannel.name: wsAPStandaloneExpectedChannel
wsAPStandaloneExpectedChannel.description: This object indicates the expected channel for the AP in standalone mode. Zero indicates that any channel is allowed.

wsAPStandaloneExpectedSecurity.name: wsAPStandaloneExpectedSecurity
wsAPStandaloneExpectedSecurity.description: This object indicates the expected security mode for the AP in standalone mode. Zero indicates that any security mode is allowed.

wsAPStandaloneExpectedSsid.name: wsAPStandaloneExpectedSsid
wsAPStandaloneExpectedSsid.description: This object indicates the expected SSID for the AP in standalone mode. A null string indicates that any SSID is allowed.

wsAPStandaloneExpectedWds.name: wsAPStandaloneExpectedWds
wsAPStandaloneExpectedWds.description: This object indicates whether the AP is allowed to operate as a bridge. Configurable values are: any Either WDS or normal mode is allowed normal - AP is not allowed to operate in WDS mode bridge - AP is only allowed to operate in WDS mode

wsAPStandaloneExpectedWired.name: wsAPStandaloneExpectedWired
wsAPStandaloneExpectedWired.description: This object indicates the expected wired network mode for the AP in standalone mode.

wsAPConfigRowStatus.name: wsAPConfigRowStatus
wsAPConfigRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the table. The supported values are: active(1) - indicates a valid entry createAndGo(4) - creates a new entry in the table destroy(6) - removes an existing entry from the table As this table is indexed by wsAPMacAddress, - to create an entry, specify the AP MAC address and set object value to createAndGo(4) - to delete an entry, select the entry from the list and set object value to destroy(6)

wsIPAddress.name: wsIPAddress
wsIPAddress.description: This object represents wireless controller IP address. When wireless mode is in disabled state, the value of controller IP address is zero.

wsOperationalStatus.name: wsOperationalStatus
wsOperationalStatus.description: Indicates the current operating status of the wireless system.

wsOperationalStatusDisableReason.name: wsOperationalStatusDisableReason
wsOperationalStatusDisableReason.description: This object indicates the reason of operational status to be disabled. Values 5 and 6 are applicable only if routing functionality present.

wsTotalPeerSwitches.name: wsTotalPeerSwitches
wsTotalPeerSwitches.description: Total number of peer controllers detected on the network.

wsTotalAPs.name: wsTotalAPs
wsTotalAPs.description: Sum of all the WS managed APs, connection failed APs, and discovered APs in the database.

wsTotalManagedAPs.name: wsTotalManagedAPs
wsTotalManagedAPs.description: Total number of WS managed APs currently authenticated to the controller.

wsTotalStandaloneAPs.name: wsTotalStandaloneAPs
wsTotalStandaloneAPs.description: Total number of trusted AP's in the standalone mode.

wsTotalDiscoveredAPs.name: wsTotalDiscoveredAPs
wsTotalDiscoveredAPs.description: Number of APs that are connected to the controller, but are not completely configured.

wsTotalConnectionFailedAPs.name: wsTotalConnectionFailedAPs
wsTotalConnectionFailedAPs.description: Number of APs that were previously authenticated and managed, but currently do not have connection with the controller.

wsTotalRogueAPs.name: wsTotalRogueAPs
wsTotalRogueAPs.description: Total number of Rogue APs detected on the WLAN.

wsTotalUnknownAPs.name: wsTotalUnknownAPs
wsTotalUnknownAPs.description: Total number of Unknown APs detected on the WLAN.

wsMaximumManagedAPsInPeerGroup.name: wsMaximumManagedAPsInPeerGroup
wsMaximumManagedAPsInPeerGroup.description: Maximum number of APs that can be managed by the wireless controller when it acts as Cluster Controller.

wsTotalClients.name: wsTotalClients
wsTotalClients.description: Total number of clients present in the network.

wsTotalAuthenticatedClients.name: wsTotalAuthenticatedClients
wsTotalAuthenticatedClients.description: Total number of authenticated clients across all APs managed by the controller.

wsMaximumAssociatedClients.name: wsMaximumAssociatedClients
wsMaximumAssociatedClients.description: Maximum number of clients that can associate with the wireless system.

wsWLANUtilization.name: wsWLANUtilization
wsWLANUtilization.description: Total network utilization across all APs managed by this controller. This is based on global statistics.

wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestAction.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestAction
wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestAction.description: This action object is used to: - start - Start the config push into all the peer controllers in the peer group. - Read on this object will always return none.

wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestStatus.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestStatus
wsGlobalPeerConfigRequestStatus.description: The global status for the configuration push operation to one or more peer controllers.

wsGlobalPeerConfigReceiveStatus.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigReceiveStatus
wsGlobalPeerConfigReceiveStatus.description: The global status when wireless configuration is received from a peer controller.

wsGlobalPeerConfigSwitchIp.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigSwitchIp
wsGlobalPeerConfigSwitchIp.description: IP Address of the last controller from which this controller received any wireless configuration data.

wsGlobalPeerConfigReceived.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigReceived
wsGlobalPeerConfigReceived.description: Indicates which portions of configuration were last received from a peer controller.

wsGlobalPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp.name: wsGlobalPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp
wsGlobalPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp.description: The last time this controller received any configuration data from a peer controller.

wsClusterControllerIndicator.name: wsClusterControllerIndicator
wsClusterControllerIndicator.description: Indicates if the controller is currently the Cluster Controller of the peer group or not.

wsClusterController.name: wsClusterController
wsClusterController.description: This object represents Cluster Controller's IP address.

wsRogueAPMitigationCount.name: wsRogueAPMitigationCount
wsRogueAPMitigationCount.description: Number of APs to which the wireless system is currently sending de-authentication messages to mitigate against rogue APs.

wsRogueAPMitigationLimit.name: wsRogueAPMitigationLimit
wsRogueAPMitigationLimit.description: Maximum number of APs for which the system can send de-authentication frames.

wsRogueAPAcknowledgeAll.name: wsRogueAPAcknowledgeAll
wsRogueAPAcknowledgeAll.description: This is a command that allows the administrator to clear out all rogue AP states in the RF Scan database

wsTotalDetectedClients.name: wsTotalDetectedClients
wsTotalDetectedClients.description: Total number of detected clients across all APs managed by the controller.

wsMaximumDetectedClients.name: wsMaximumDetectedClients
wsMaximumDetectedClients.description: Maximum number of clients that can be maintained by the detected clients database.

wsMaximumDetectedClientPreAuthentication.name: wsMaximumDetectedClientPreAuthenticationHistoryEntries
wsMaximumDetectedClientPreAuthentication.description: Maximum number of pre-authentication history entries that can be recorded for all the detected clients present in the detected client database.

wsTotalDetectedClientPreAuthenticationHi.name: wsTotalDetectedClientPreAuthenticationHistoryEntries
wsTotalDetectedClientPreAuthenticationHi.description: Total number of pre-authentication history entries accumulated for all the detected clients present in the detected client database.

wsMaximumDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntrie.name: wsMaximumDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntries
wsMaximumDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntrie.description: Maximum number of roam history entries that can be recorded for all the detected clients present in the detected client database.

wsTotalDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntries.name: wsTotalDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntries
wsTotalDetectedClientRoamHistoryEntries.description: Total number of roam history entries accumulated for all the detected clients present in the detected client database.

wsRegenerateX509CertificateAction.name: wsRegenerateX509CertificateAction
wsRegenerateX509CertificateAction.description: This action object is used to: - start - Start the certificate regeneration on the controller. - Read on this object will always return none.

wsNetworkMutualAuthenticationStatus.name: wsNetworkMutualAuthenticationStatus
wsNetworkMutualAuthenticationStatus.description: Status of the mutual authentication enable/disable command. When status is Complete With Errors then the administrator may need to provision some controllers or APs separately.

wsTotalProvisioningAPs.name: wsTotalProvisioningAPs
wsTotalProvisioningAPs.description: Total number of APs present in the AP Provisioning database.

wsMaximumProvisioningAPs.name: wsMaximumProvisioningAPs
wsMaximumProvisioningAPs.description: Maximum number of APs that can be maintained in the AP Provisioning database.

wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitted.name: wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitted
wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted across all APs managed by this controller.

wsTotalWLANBytesRecvd.name: wsTotalWLANBytesRecvd
wsTotalWLANBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received across all APs managed by by this controller.

wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitted.name: wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitted
wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted across all APs managed by this controller.

wsTotalWLANPktsRecvd.name: wsTotalWLANPktsRecvd
wsTotalWLANPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received across all APs managed by this controller.

wsAllStatisticsReset.name: wsAllStatisticsReset
wsAllStatisticsReset.description: When we set this object to enable, all statistics maintained by controller will be cleared. Read on this object will always return disable.

wsAllStatisticsResetStatus.name: wsAllStatisticsResetStatus
wsAllStatisticsResetStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of controller statistics reset request. Default value is not started.

wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitDropped.name: wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitDropped
wsTotalWLANBytesTransmitDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction across all APs managed by this controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsTotalWLANBytesRecvDropped.name: wsTotalWLANBytesRecvDropped
wsTotalWLANBytesRecvDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction across all APs managed by this controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from AP to client.

wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitDropped.name: wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitDropped
wsTotalWLANPktsTransmitDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction across all APs managed by this controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsTotalWLANPktsRecvDropped.name: wsTotalWLANPktsRecvDropped
wsTotalWLANPktsRecvDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the receive direction across all APs managed by this controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from AP to client.

wsTotalWLANDistTunnelPktsTransmitted.name: wsTotalWLANDistTunnelPktsTransmitted
wsTotalWLANDistTunnelPktsTransmitted.description: Total number of packets transmitted by all APs using distributed tunnels.

wsTotalWLANDistTunnelRoamedClients.name: wsTotalWLANDistTunnelRoamedClients
wsTotalWLANDistTunnelRoamedClients.description: Number of clients in all APs currently in roaming state using distributed tunnels.

wsTotalWLANDistTunnelClientDenials.name: wsTotalWLANDistTunnelClientDenials
wsTotalWLANDistTunnelClientDenials.description: Number of client tunnel setups denied for all APs.

wsPeerConfigurationGlobal.name: wsPeerConfigurationGlobal
wsPeerConfigurationGlobal.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send global configuration parameters to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationDiscovery.name: wsPeerConfigurationDiscovery
wsPeerConfigurationDiscovery.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send discovery configuration parameters to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationAPDatabase.name: wsPeerConfigurationAPDatabase
wsPeerConfigurationAPDatabase.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send valid AP Database to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationChannelPower.name: wsPeerConfigurationChannelPower
wsPeerConfigurationChannelPower.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send Channel and Power configuration to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationAPProfiles.name: wsPeerConfigurationAPProfiles
wsPeerConfigurationAPProfiles.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send all AP profiles and networks to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationKnownClients.name: wsPeerConfigurationKnownClients
wsPeerConfigurationKnownClients.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send configured known client entries to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationCaptivePortal.name: wsPeerConfigurationCaptivePortal
wsPeerConfigurationCaptivePortal.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send all Captive Portal configuration to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationRadiusClient.name: wsPeerConfigurationRadiusClient
wsPeerConfigurationRadiusClient.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send RADIUS Client configuration parameters to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationQosAcl.name: wsPeerConfigurationQosAcl
wsPeerConfigurationQosAcl.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send all QoS ACL configuration to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationQosDiffServ.name: wsPeerConfigurationQosDiffServ
wsPeerConfigurationQosDiffServ.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send all QoS DiffServ configuration to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationWdsGroup.name: wsPeerConfigurationWdsGroup
wsPeerConfigurationWdsGroup.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send configured wds groups to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsPeerConfigurationDeviceLocation.name: wsPeerConfigurationDeviceLocation
wsPeerConfigurationDeviceLocation.description: Flag to enable/disable the functionality to send configured device location parameters to a peer controller on a configuration push.

wsClusterPriority.name: wsClusterPriority
wsClusterPriority.description: Preference level of the controller to become the Cluster Controller of the Peer Group.A priority of 0 means that the controller can not become cluster controller.

wsAPClientQosMode.name: wsAPClientQosMode
wsAPClientQosMode.description: Flag to globally enable/disable AP quality-of-service operation for wireless clients.

wsAPAutoUpgradeMode.name: wsAPAutoUpgradeMode
wsAPAutoUpgradeMode.description: Flag to enable/disable AP auto upgrade mode. This object is configurable only if the wireless controller supports both 'Integrated' and 'Independent' AP image download modes. If the controller supports only 'Integrated' mode, the default is Enable.

wsDistTunnelIdleTimeout.name: wsDistTunnelIdleTimeout
wsDistTunnelIdleTimeout.description: Time of inactivity in seconds to wait before terminating a tunnel client.

wsDistTunnelMaxTimeout.name: wsDistTunnelMaxTimeout
wsDistTunnelMaxTimeout.description: Time in seconds to wait before terminating a tunnel client.

wsDistTunnelMaxMcastRepl.name: wsDistTunnelMaxMcastRepl
wsDistTunnelMaxMcastRepl.description: Maximum number of multicast replications that can be performed by the AP.

wsDistTunnelMaxClients.name: wsDistTunnelMaxClients
wsDistTunnelMaxClients.description: Maximum number of clients that can use tunneled through a Home AP.

wsMACAuthenticationMode.name: wsMACAuthenticationMode
wsMACAuthenticationMode.description: This object indicates whether MAC addresses in the Known Client database are granted or denied access if they are in the list, but dont have a specific action.

wsKnownClientTable.name: wsKnownClientTable
wsKnownClientTable.description: This table contains entries of the known clients.

wsKnownClientEntry.name: wsKnownClientEntry
wsKnownClientEntry.description: The entry contains parameters of a known client.

wsKnownClientMacAddress.name: wsKnownClientMacAddress
wsKnownClientMacAddress.description: MAC address of the known client.

wsKnownClientAuthAction.name: wsKnownClientAuthAction
wsKnownClientAuthAction.description: This object indicates whether to grant, deny, or use global action for client authentication.

wsKnownClientName.name: wsKnownClientName
wsKnownClientName.description: Descriptive name of the known client.

wsKnownClientRowStatus.name: wsKnownClientRowStatus
wsKnownClientRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in this table.

rogueAdminConfig.name: rogueAdminConfig
rogueAdminConfig.description: Report the AP as rogue in the RF Scan if the local database indicates that the AP is rogue. Can not be disabled.

rogueUnknownApManagedSsid.name: rogueUnknownApManagedSsid
rogueUnknownApManagedSsid.description: Enable rogue reporting for unknown AP's detected with a managed SSID.

rogueFakeManagedApManagedSsid.name: rogueFakeManagedApManagedSsid
rogueFakeManagedApManagedSsid.description: Enable rogue reporting for fake managed AP's detected with a managed SSID.

rogueManagedApNoSsid.name: rogueManagedApNoSsid
rogueManagedApNoSsid.description: Enable rogue reporting of all APs detected with no SSID.

rogueManagedApInvalidChannel.name: rogueManagedApInvalidChannel
rogueManagedApInvalidChannel.description: Enable rogue reporting of fake managed AP's detected with an invalid channel.

rogueManagedSsidInvalidSecurity.name: rogueManagedSsidInvalidSecurity
rogueManagedSsidInvalidSecurity.description: Enable rogue reporting of AP's detected with managed SSID's and an invalid security configuration.

rogueManagedApInvalidSsid.name: rogueManagedApInvalidSsid
rogueManagedApInvalidSsid.description: Enable rogue reporting of managed AP's with an invalid SSID.

rogueApIllegalChannel.name: rogueApIllegalChannel
rogueApIllegalChannel.description: Enable rogue reporting of AP's operating on an illegal channel.

rogueStandaloneApInvalidConfig.name: rogueStandaloneApInvalidConfig
rogueStandaloneApInvalidConfig.description: Enable rogue reporting of standalone AP's operating with an unexpected configuration.

rogueUnexpectedWdsDevice.name: rogueUnexpectedWdsDevice
rogueUnexpectedWdsDevice.description: Enable rogue reporting of unexpected WDS devices.

rogueUnmanagedApWiredNetwork.name: rogueUnmanagedApWiredNetwork
rogueUnmanagedApWiredNetwork.description: Enable rogue reporting of unmanaged AP's on a wired network.

wiredNetworkDetectionInterval.name: wiredNetworkDetectionInterval
wiredNetworkDetectionInterval.description: Minimum number of seconds that the AP waits before starting a new wired network detection cycle. A value of 0 disables wired network detection.

rogueDetectedTrapInterval.name: rogueDetectedTrapInterval
rogueDetectedTrapInterval.description: The interval in seconds between transmissions of the trap telling the administrator that Rogues are present in the RF Scan database. A configured value of 0 disables the trap from being sent. .

rogueDetectedTrapIntvl.name: rogueDetectedTrapIntvl
rogueDetectedTrapIntvl.description: The interval in seconds between transmissions of the trap telling the administrator that Rogues are present in the Rogue Clients are present in the Detected Clients Database. A configured value of 0 disables the trap from being sent.

knownClientDatabaseTest.name: knownClientDatabaseTest
knownClientDatabaseTest.description: Report the client as rogue if it fails the Known Client Database Test.

authReqTransmitRate.name: authReqTransmitRate
authReqTransmitRate.description: Report the client as rogue if it exceeds configured rate for transmitting 802.11 authentication requests.

probeReqTransmitRate.name: probeReqTransmitRate
probeReqTransmitRate.description: Report the client as rogue if it exceeds configured rate for transmitting probe requests.

deauthReqTransmitRate.name: deauthReqTransmitRate
deauthReqTransmitRate.description: Report the client as rogue if it exceeds configured rate for transmitting 802.11 deauthentication requests.

maxFailingAuthentication.name: maxFailingAuthentication
maxFailingAuthentication.description: Report the client as rogue if it exceeds maximum number of failing authentications.

authWithUnknownAP.name: authWithUnknownAP
authWithUnknownAP.description: Report the client as rogue if it is authenticated with an unknown AP.

clientThreatMitigation.name: clientThreatMitigation
clientThreatMitigation.description: Transmission of de-authentication messages to known clients associated with unknown APs. The Known Client test must also be enabled in order for the mitigation to take place.

deauthThresholdInterval.name: deauthThresholdInterval
deauthThresholdInterval.description: Number of seconds for counting the de-authentication messages.

deauthThresholdValue.name: deauthThresholdValue
deauthThresholdValue.description: If controller receives more than specified de-auth messages during the threshold interval the test triggers the client to be reported as rogue.

authThresholdInterval.name: authThresholdInterval
authThresholdInterval.description: Number of seconds for counting the authentication messages.

authThresholdValue.name: authThresholdValue
authThresholdValue.description: If controller receives more than specified auth messages during the threshold interval the test triggers the client to be reported as rogue.

probeThresholdInterval.name: probeThresholdInterval
probeThresholdInterval.description: Number of seconds for counting the probe messages.

probeThresholdValue.name: probeThresholdValue
probeThresholdValue.description: If controller receives more than specified probe messages during the threshold interval the test triggers the client to be reported as rogue.

authFailureThreshold.name: authFailureThreshold
authFailureThreshold.description: The number of 802.1X authentication failures that triggers the client to be reported as rogue.

knownClientDatabaseLocation.name: knownClientDatabaseLocation
knownClientDatabaseLocation.description: The location of Known Client Database. If the value is local then Known Client Database is located in the local controller. Otherwise the database is located in the RADIUS Server.

knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerName.name: knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerName
knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerName.description: Name of the RADIUS server used for Known Client database This is used when knownClientDatabaseLocation is set to 'radius'.

knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerStatus.name: knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerStatus
knownClientDatabaseRadiusServerStatus.description: Indicates whether the specified named RADIUS Authentication server is configured in the RADIUS Client configuration.

notInOUIDatabase.name: notInOUIDatabase
notInOUIDatabase.description: Report the client as rogue if it's OUI is not present in the OUI Database.

wsAuthRadiusServerName.name: wsAuthRadiusServerName
wsAuthRadiusServerName.description: Name of the RADIUS server used for AP authentications as well as client authentications when a network-level RADIUS server is not defined.

wsAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatus.name: wsAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatus
wsAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatus.description: Indicates whether the specified named RADIUS Authentication server is configured in the RADIUS Client configuration.

wsAcctRadiusServerName.name: wsAcctRadiusServerName
wsAcctRadiusServerName.description: Name of the RADIUS server used for reporting wireless client associations and disassociations when a network-level RADIUS accounting server is not defined.

wsAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatus.name: wsAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatus
wsAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatus.description: Indicates whether the specified named RADIUS Accounting server is configured in the RADIUS Client configuration.

wsRadiusAcctMode.name: wsRadiusAcctMode
wsRadiusAcctMode.description: Flag to indicate whether or not RADIUS accounting is enabled for wireless clients.

wsAutoIPAssignMode.name: wsAutoIPAssignMode
wsAutoIPAssignMode.description: Flag indicating whether the Wireless feature should automatically assign an IP address from one of the active interfaces or whether the IP address is manually assigned.

wsSwitchStaticIPAddress.name: wsSwitchStaticIPAddress
wsSwitchStaticIPAddress.description: Statically assigned IPv4 address for the Wireless feature. If Auto IP Assignment is true then this setting is ignored.

wsTspecViolationReportInterval.name: wsTspecViolationReportInterval
wsTspecViolationReportInterval.description: Specifies the time period at which wireless clients detected as using admission-controlled resources without proper TSPEC authorization are reported via the system logging and SNMP trap mechanisms. If a violating client disassociates before the next report interval, it is reported upon disassociation. This object is specified in seconds, with a default value of 300 (5 minutes). Setting this object value to 0 disables TSPEC violation reporting.

wsSwitchStatusTable.name: wsSwitchStatusTable
wsSwitchStatusTable.description: This table contain access point and client status parameters of peer controllers of wireless controller.

wsSwitchStatusEntry.name: wsSwitchStatusEntry
wsSwitchStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the access point and client status parameters of each peer of wireless controller.

wsSwitchIPAddress.name: wsSwitchIPAddress
wsSwitchIPAddress.description: This object represents wireless controller IP address. When wireless mode is in disabled state, return entry will be none.

wsSwitchClusterPriority.name: wsSwitchClusterPriority
wsSwitchClusterPriority.description: Preference level of the controller to become the Cluster Controller of the Peer Group.

wsSwitchAPImageDownloadMode.name: wsSwitchAPImageDownloadMode
wsSwitchAPImageDownloadMode.description: The AP image download mode supported by the wireless controller. The displayed mode can be one of the following: Integrated - The controller supports Integrated mode. In this mode, the AP code is located on the controller, and the controller automatically updates the code on APs it manages. Independent - The controller supports Independent mode. In this mode, the AP code is on a TFTP server, and the download is triggered from the cluster controller. Integrated, Independent - The controller supports both modes. Note that this field displays the mode only if wireless controllers that support Independent and Integrated AP Image Download modes co-exist in the network.

wsSwitchTotalAPs.name: wsSwitchTotalAPs
wsSwitchTotalAPs.description: Sum of all the WS managed APs, connection failed APs, and discovered APs in the database of specified controller.

wsSwitchManagedAPs.name: wsSwitchManagedAPs
wsSwitchManagedAPs.description: Total number of WS managed APs currently authenticated, configured and have an active connection with the specifed controller.

wsSwitchDiscoveredAPs.name: wsSwitchDiscoveredAPs
wsSwitchDiscoveredAPs.description: Number of APs that are connected to the specified controller, but have not been completely configured.

wsSwitchConnectionFailedAPs.name: wsSwitchConnectionFailedAPs
wsSwitchConnectionFailedAPs.description: Number of APs that were previously authenticated and managed, but currently do not have connection with the specified controller.

wsSwitchMaximumManagedAPs.name: wsSwitchMaximumManagedAPs
wsSwitchMaximumManagedAPs.description: Maximum number of APs that the specified controller can manage.

wsSwitchTotalClients.name: wsSwitchTotalClients
wsSwitchTotalClients.description: Total number of clients in the database that include clients with an associated, authenticated and disassociated status.

wsSwitchAuthenticatedClients.name: wsSwitchAuthenticatedClients
wsSwitchAuthenticatedClients.description: Total number of authenticated clients across all APs managed by the specified controller.

wsSwitchWLANUtilization.name: wsSwitchWLANUtilization
wsSwitchWLANUtilization.description: Total network utilization across all APs managed by the specifed controller.

wsSwitchDistTunnelClients.name: wsSwitchDistTunnelClients
wsSwitchDistTunnelClients.description: Number of clients that are currently sending and receiving packets via distributed tunnels.

wsSwitchStatisticsTable.name: wsSwitchStatisticsTable
wsSwitchStatisticsTable.description: This table contain WLAN statistics for every controller in the peer group. Only Cluster Controller can hold the entries for peer controllers. The controller which is not a Cluster Controller only keep statistics local to it.

wsSwitchStatisticsEntry.name: wsSwitchStatisticsEntry
wsSwitchStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry describe WLAN statistics of specified controller in the wireless system.

wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitted.name: wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitted
wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted across all APs managed by the specified controller.

wsSwitchWLANBytesReceived.name: wsSwitchWLANBytesReceived
wsSwitchWLANBytesReceived.description: Total bytes received across all APs managed by the specified controller.

wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitted.name: wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitted
wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted across all APs managed by the specified controller.

wsSwitchWLANPktsReceived.name: wsSwitchWLANPktsReceived
wsSwitchWLANPktsReceived.description: Total packets received across all APs managed by the specified controller.

wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitDropped.name: wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitDropped
wsSwitchWLANBytesTransmitDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction across all APs managed by the specified controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsSwitchWLANBytesRecvDropped.name: wsSwitchWLANBytesRecvDropped
wsSwitchWLANBytesRecvDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction across all APs managed the specified controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from AP to client.

wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitDropped.name: wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitDropped
wsSwitchWLANPktsTransmitDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction across all APs managed by the specified controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsSwitchWLANPktsRecvDropped.name: wsSwitchWLANPktsRecvDropped
wsSwitchWLANPktsRecvDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the receive direction across all APs managed by the specified controller. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from AP to client.

networkMutualAuthMode.name: networkMutualAuthMode
networkMutualAuthMode.description: Flag to enable/disable mutual authentication of the Wireless controllers and Access Points in the network.

unmanagedAPReprovisioning.name: unmanagedAPReprovisioning
unmanagedAPReprovisioning.description: Flag to enable/disable reprovisioning of APs when in unmanaged mode.

apProvisionDbAgeTime.name: apProvisionDbAgeTime
apProvisionDbAgeTime.description: Time in hours to wait without hearing any updates for the APs before removing them from the provisioning database.A value of 0 in input range means that the entry never ages out.

devLocRfScanLocMode.name: devLocRfScanLocMode
devLocRfScanLocMode.description: Flag to enable/disable RF Scan location Mode.

devLocRfScanLocInterval.name: devLocRfScanLocInterval
devLocRfScanLocInterval.description: Number of seconds between iterations of triangulation table device location protocol.

wsIPPollMode.name: wsIPPollMode
wsIPPollMode.description: Flag to enable/disable IP based discovery of APs and peer controllers.

wsL2DiscoveryMode.name: wsL2DiscoveryMode
wsL2DiscoveryMode.description: Flag to enable/disable L2 discovery of APs and peer controllers.

wsIPPollListTable.name: wsIPPollListTable
wsIPPollListTable.description: This table contains IP addresses to poll on the network.

wsIPPollListEntry.name: wsIPPollListEntry
wsIPPollListEntry.description: An IP address list that can be configured globally on the wireless controller to define which IP addresses to poll in order to discover new APs and peer controllers. This list is used when discovery via IP Polling is enabled.

wsPollIpAddress.name: wsPollIpAddress
wsPollIpAddress.description: IP address of an AP or controller to poll.

wsPollIPStatus.name: wsPollIPStatus
wsPollIPStatus.description: Indicates whether or not the controller reached this IP address.

wsIPPollRowStatus.name: wsIPPollRowStatus
wsIPPollRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete entries in the table.

wsL2DiscoveryVlanListTable.name: wsL2DiscoveryVlanListTable
wsL2DiscoveryVlanListTable.description: This table contains the list of VLANs on which to send L2 discovery multicast packets.

wsL2DiscoveryVlanListEntry.name: wsL2DiscoveryVlanListEntry
wsL2DiscoveryVlanListEntry.description: A list of VLANs on which to send L2 discovery multicast frames when L2 broadcast discovery mode is enabled. The entries in this table are limited to sixteen. By default there will be one entry in this table with wsL2DiscoveryVlanId equal to one. This entry can neither be created nor deleted.

wsL2DiscoveryVlanId.name: wsL2DiscoveryVlanId
wsL2DiscoveryVlanId.description: VLAN Id on which controller will send L2 discovery multicast frames.

wsL2DiscoveryVlanRowStatus.name: wsL2DiscoveryVlanRowStatus
wsL2DiscoveryVlanRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create and delete entries in the table.

wsIPPollListMaxNumOfEntries.name: wsIPPollListMaxNumOfEntries
wsIPPollListMaxNumOfEntries.description: Maximum number of IP discovery entries allowed to be configured.

wsIPPollListNumOfConfigEntries.name: wsIPPollListNumOfConfigEntries
wsIPPollListNumOfConfigEntries.description: Total number of entries configured IP discovery entries.

wsIPPollListNumOfPolledEntries.name: wsIPPollListNumOfPolledEntries
wsIPPollListNumOfPolledEntries.description: Total number of polled entries in the IP discovery list.

wsIPPollListNumOfNotPolledEntries.name: wsIPPollListNumOfNotPolledEntries
wsIPPollListNumOfNotPolledEntries.description: Total number of not-polled entries in the IP discovery list.

wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredEntries.name: wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredEntries
wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredEntries.description: Total number of discovered entries in the IP discovery list.

wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredFailedEntries.name: wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredFailedEntries
wsIPPollListNumOfDiscoveredFailedEntries.description: Total number of discovered-failed entries in the IP discovery list.

wsL2CentTnnlVlanListTable.name: wsL2CentTnnlVlanListTable
wsL2CentTnnlVlanListTable.description: This table contains the list of layer 2 tunneled VLANs.

wsL2CentTnnlVlanListEntry.name: wsL2CentTnnlVlanListEntry
wsL2CentTnnlVlanListEntry.description: A list of VLANs on which all frames are tunneled. The entries in this table are limited to 64.

wsL2CentTnnlVlanId.name: wsL2CentTnnlVlanId
wsL2CentTnnlVlanId.description: VLAN ID on which all frames are tunneled.

wsL2CentTnnlVlanRowStatus.name: wsL2CentTnnlVlanRowStatus
wsL2CentTnnlVlanRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create and delete entries in the table.

wsOuiTable.name: wsOuiTable
wsOuiTable.description: This table contains the list of OUIs that have been configured by the administrator. The entries in this table are limited to 64.

wsOuiEntry.name: wsOuiEntry
wsOuiEntry.description: A list of OUIs. Each entry contains OUI and descriptive name of the wireless device manufacturer. The administrator can enter up to 64 user-defined OUIs.

wsOuiValue.name: wsOuiValue
wsOuiValue.description: The OUI value for the AP or the client. Least significant bit of the first byte must be zero.

wsOuiDescription.name: wsOuiDescription
wsOuiDescription.description: The descriptive name for the manufacturer of AP or wireless client adapter.

wsOuiRowStatus.name: wsOuiRowStatus
wsOuiRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create and delete entries in the table.

wsAPProfileTable.name: wsAPProfileTable
wsAPProfileTable.description: The following parameters can be configured within an AP configuration profile. A profile is used to replicate a single AP configuration across multiple managed APs. Modification or deletion is not allowed if the profile is assigned to one or more managed APs except wsCopyAPProfileToProfileId.

wsAPProfileEntry.name: wsAPProfileEntry
wsAPProfileEntry.description: Each entry has parameters that can be configured within an AP configuration profile. A profile is used to replicate a single AP configuration across multiple managed APs, and is indexed by an integer Id.

wsAPProfileId.name: wsAPProfileId
wsAPProfileId.description: Unique AP Profile Id for each entry.

wsAPProfileState.name: wsAPProfileState
wsAPProfileState.description: Indicates current state of AP Profile.

wsAPProfileRowStatus.name: wsAPProfileRowStatus
wsAPProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create or delete entries in the table.

wsCopyAPProfileToProfileId.name: wsCopyAPProfileToProfileId
wsCopyAPProfileToProfileId.description: This object copies the AP profile configuration to the specified valid AP Profile Id. If specified Profile Id is already assigned to one or more managed APs, the operation is not allowed. Read on this object will always return zero.

wsAPProfileApply.name: wsAPProfileApply
wsAPProfileApply.description: This object is used to apply the AP profile configuration. Read on this object will always return none.

wsAPHardwareTypeID.name: wsAPHardwareTypeID
wsAPHardwareTypeID.description: AP Hardware type ID associated with each entry.

wsAPWiredDetectionVlanId.name: wsAPWiredDetectionVlanId
wsAPWiredDetectionVlanId.description: VLAN ID that is used to send packets on the wire that enable the system to discover rogue APs attached to the wired network.

wsAPProfileDisconnAPFwdingMode.name: wsAPProfileDisconnAPFwdingMode
wsAPProfileDisconnAPFwdingMode.description: Flag to enable/disable Disconnected AP Data Forwarding Mode.

wsAPProfileDisconnAPMgmtMode.name: wsAPProfileDisconnAPMgmtMode
wsAPProfileDisconnAPMgmtMode.description: Flag to enable/disable Disconnected AP Management Mode.

wsAPProfileAeroScoutSupportMode.name: wsAPProfileAeroScoutSupportMode
wsAPProfileAeroScoutSupportMode.description: Flag to enable/disable AE Protocol Support Mode.

wsAPProfileRadioTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioTable
wsAPProfileRadioTable.description: This table contains parameters that can be configured with in an AP Profile per radio interface.

wsAPProfileRadioEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioEntry
wsAPProfileRadioEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents parameters that can be configured with in an AP profile per radio interface. Two entries in this table will get created automatically for each AP profile being created in wsAPProfileTable. Whenever AP profile entry is deleted, corresponding radio profile entries will get deleted automatically.

wsAPRadioAdminMode.name: wsAPRadioAdminMode
wsAPRadioAdminMode.description: Flag to indicate whether the radio is operational.

wsAPRadioFrequency.name: wsAPRadioFrequency
wsAPRadioFrequency.description: Indicates which physical layer technology to use on radio. Default value for radio 1 is 'ieee802dot11bgn' and default value for radio 2 is 'ieee802dot11an'.

wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanMode.name: wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanMode
wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanMode.description: When Sentry mode is disabled this flag controls whether the radio moves away from the operating channel while doing scans. When this mode is disabled the radio scans only on the operating channel. When sentry mode is enabled on the radio this parameter is ignored.

wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanInterval.name: wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanInterval
wsAPRadioOtherChannelsScanInterval.description: If scan mode is enable, indicates how often the radio leaves its operational channel.

wsAPRadioSentryScanMode.name: wsAPRadioSentryScanMode
wsAPRadioSentryScanMode.description: When Sentry mode is enabled the radio doesn't do any data forwarding, but only periodically scan channels for rogues. The length of time spent on each channels controlled by the 'scan duration' time.

wsAPRadioSentryScanChannel.name: wsAPRadioSentryScanChannel
wsAPRadioSentryScanChannel.description: If scanning is enabled, this object indicates on which frequencies to scan.

wsAPRadioScanDuration.name: wsAPRadioScanDuration
wsAPRadioScanDuration.description: Indicates how long the radio can scan before returning to its operational channel. The default value is 10ms.

wsAPRadioRateLimitMode.name: wsAPRadioRateLimitMode
wsAPRadioRateLimitMode.description: This object enables/disables rate limit for broadcast and multicast traffic transmitted across the network.

wsAPRadioRateLimit.name: wsAPRadioRateLimit
wsAPRadioRateLimit.description: Allowed rate limit for broadcast/multicast traffic transmitted across the network. Broadcast/multicast traffic below this limit is transmitted normally.

wsAPRadioRateLimitBurst.name: wsAPRadioRateLimitBurst
wsAPRadioRateLimitBurst.description: Broadcast/multicast traffic can occur in bursts up to this value before all traffic is considered to exceed the limit.

wsAPRadioBeaconInterval.name: wsAPRadioBeaconInterval
wsAPRadioBeaconInterval.description: Interval at which the AP transmit beacon frames.

wsAPRadioDTIMPeriod.name: wsAPRadioDTIMPeriod
wsAPRadioDTIMPeriod.description: Indicates the number of beacons between Delivery Traffic Indication MAP(DTIM). DTIM indicates buffered broadcast/multicast traffic on an AP.

wsAPRadioFragmentationThreshold.name: wsAPRadioFragmentationThreshold
wsAPRadioFragmentationThreshold.description: This object limits the size of packets transmitted over the network. Only even values are allowed in the defined range.

wsAPRadioRTSThreshold.name: wsAPRadioRTSThreshold
wsAPRadioRTSThreshold.description: This object indicates the number of octets in an MAC Protocol Data Unit(MPDU), below which an request to send(RTS)/clear to send(CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

wsAPRadioShortRetryLimit.name: wsAPRadioShortRetryLimit
wsAPRadioShortRetryLimit.description: This object indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts on frame sizes less than or equal to the RTS threshold. Set action for this object will be supported in next release.

wsAPRadioLongRetryLimit.name: wsAPRadioLongRetryLimit
wsAPRadioLongRetryLimit.description: This object indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts on frame sizes greater than the RTS threshold. Set action for this object will be supported in next release.

wsAPRadioMaxTransmitLifetime.name: wsAPRadioMaxTransmitLifetime
wsAPRadioMaxTransmitLifetime.description: This object indicates the elapsed time after the initial transmission of MAC Service Data Unit(MSDU), after which further attempts to transmit the MSDU shall be terminated. Set action for this object will be supported in next release.

wsAPRadioMaxReceiveLifetime.name: wsAPRadioMaxReceiveLifetime
wsAPRadioMaxReceiveLifetime.description: This object indicates the elapsed time after the initial reception of a fragmented MAC Management Protocol Data Unit(MMPDU) or MSDU, after which further attempts to reassemble the MMPDU or MSDU shall be terminated. Set action for this object will be supported in next release.

wsAPRadioMaxClients.name: wsAPRadioMaxClients
wsAPRadioMaxClients.description: Maximum number of client stations that can simultaneously get associated on this interface.

wsAPRadioAutoPowerMode.name: wsAPRadioAutoPowerMode
wsAPRadioAutoPowerMode.description: Flag to indicate power is automatically adjusted by the controller.

wsAPRadioTxPower.name: wsAPRadioTxPower
wsAPRadioTxPower.description: If auto power mode is disabled, this object indicates a fixed power setting for the radio.

wsAPRadioWMMMode.name: wsAPRadioWMMMode
wsAPRadioWMMMode.description: Flag to enable/disable Wi-Fi MultiMedia Mode. When enabled, QOS settings affect both downstream traffic to the sation and upstream traffic to the AP. When disabled, QOS only applies to downstream traffic.

wsAPRadioLoadBalancingMode.name: wsAPRadioLoadBalancingMode
wsAPRadioLoadBalancingMode.description: Flag to indicate that AP will load balance users on this radio.

wsAPRadioUtilization.name: wsAPRadioUtilization
wsAPRadioUtilization.description: If load balancing is enabled, percentage of network utilization allowed on the radio before clients are denied. This value is displayed in percentage.

wsAPRadioAutoChannelMode.name: wsAPRadioAutoChannelMode
wsAPRadioAutoChannelMode.description: Flag to indicate whether initial AP radio channel assignment can be automatically adjusted by controller due to changes in radio performance.

wsAPRadioStationIsolationMode.name: wsAPRadioStationIsolationMode
wsAPRadioStationIsolationMode.description: Flag to indicate whether Station Isolation is enabled on the Radio.

wsAPRadioPrimaryChannel.name: wsAPRadioPrimaryChannel
wsAPRadioPrimaryChannel.description: Specify relative location of Primary Channel in the 40 MHz channel.

wsAPRadioShortGuardInterval.name: wsAPRadioShortGuardInterval
wsAPRadioShortGuardInterval.description: Dead time, in nanoseconds, between OFDM symbols which prevents Inter-Symbol and Inter-Carrier Interference (ISI, ICI). The short guard interval, when enabled, is 400ns and the standard guard interval, when disabled, is 800ns.

wsAPRadioSTBCMode.name: wsAPRadioSTBCMode
wsAPRadioSTBCMode.description: The Space Time Block Code (STBC) Mode enables the AP to send the same data stream on multiple antennas at the same time. This is different from MIMO where the data stream is divided between two antennas.

wsAPRadioMulticastTxRate.name: wsAPRadioMulticastTxRate
wsAPRadioMulticastTxRate.description: Indicates the data rate AP will send multicast data to its client stations represented by a count from 2 - 127, corresponding to data rates in multiples of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s. 0 represents automatic rate selection. For Example : Supported Data Rate Mbps 2 1 4 2 11 5.5 12 6 18 9 and so on.

wsAPRadioNoAckMode.name: wsAPRadioNoAckMode
wsAPRadioNoAckMode.description: Don't send acknowledgement to correctly received frames.

wsAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled.name: wsAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled
wsAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled.description: Flag to enable/disable Radio Resource Management (RRM) as defined in the IEEE 802.11k specification. RRM allows wireless clients to request adjustments and report conditions regarding channel load and neighbor detection.

wsAPRadioQOSEDCATemplate.name: wsAPRadioQOSEDCATemplate
wsAPRadioQOSEDCATemplate.description: This object indicates the QOS template choice in effect for the profile and radio.

wsAPRadioMinTxPower.name: wsAPRadioMinTxPower
wsAPRadioMinTxPower.description: Minimum Transmit Power that can be set by APA on the radio. Default Value is 20% for 2.4Ghz Radio and 100% for 5Ghz radio.

wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesTable
wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesTable.description: This table represents the supported data rates by AP Profile.

wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesEntry
wsAPProfileRadioSupportedRatesEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents supported data rate.

wsSupportedDataRate.name: wsSupportedDataRate
wsSupportedDataRate.description: Indicates the data rate, AP will actually support in setting up communications with client stations represented by a count from 2 - 127, corresponding to data rates in multiples of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s. Supported Data Rate Mbps 2 1 4 2 11 5.5 12 6 18 9 and so on.

wsAPProfileRadioSupportedDataMode.name: wsAPProfileRadioSupportedDataMode
wsAPProfileRadioSupportedDataMode.description: Displays supported data rate by an AP Profile. Supported rates by an AP Profile depends on physical mode of the radio.

wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesTable
wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesTable.description: This table represents the basic data rates advertised by an AP Profile.Stations connecting to this AP must support this set of data rates.

wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesEntry
wsAPProfileRadioBasicRatesEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents basic data rate.

wsBasicDataRate.name: wsBasicDataRate
wsBasicDataRate.description: Indicates the basic data rate, AP will actually advertise to its client stations represented by a count from 2 - 127, corresponding to data rates in multiples of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 63.5 Mbit/s. For Example : Supported Data Rate Mbps 2 1 4 2 11 5.5 12 6 18 9 and so on.

wsAPProfileRadioBasicDataMode.name: wsAPProfileRadioBasicDataMode
wsAPProfileRadioBasicDataMode.description: Displays basic data rate advertised by an AP Profile. Basic rate depends on physical mode of the radio.

wsAPProfileVAPTable.name: wsAPProfileVAPTable
wsAPProfileVAPTable.description: This table is about VAP profile configuration. When AP profile entry is created, corresponding eight VAP entries will get created for each radio. When AP Profile entry is get deleted, corresponding VAP entries will be deleted automatically.

wsAPProfileVAPEntry.name: wsAPProfileVAPEntry
wsAPProfileVAPEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents VAP profile.

wsVAPId.name: wsVAPId
wsVAPId.description: Index of the VAP with respect to the radio interface.

wsVAPMode.name: wsVAPMode
wsVAPMode.description: Flag to enable/disable VAP. VAP0 can not be disabled. In order to disable VAP0, radio must be turned off.

wsVAPNetworkId.name: wsVAPNetworkId
wsVAPNetworkId.description: Network configuration assigned to the VAP. By default, VAP 0 to 7 are assigned to Network Ids 1 to 8 in order.

wsAPProfileQOSTable.name: wsAPProfileQOSTable
wsAPProfileQOSTable.description: This table displays QOS configuration. Enhanced Distributed Channel Access(EDCA) parameters of an AP affect downstream traffic from AP to the client station. Station EDCA parameters affect upstream traffic from the client station to an AP. Creation of AP Profile creates corresponding four qos profiles with default values for each radio. Deletion of AP Profile deletes the corresponding QOS entries in this table.

wsAPProfileQOSEntry.name: wsAPProfileQOSEntry
wsAPProfileQOSEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents QOS profile.

wsQOSQueueId.name: wsQOSQueueId
wsQOSQueueId.description: This object indicates QOS Queue Id.

wsAPEDCAAIFS.name: wsAPEDCAAIFS
wsAPEDCAAIFS.description: Specifies the wait time for data frames. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 1 msec video(1) - 1 msec besteffort(2) - 3 msec background(3) - 7 msec

wsAPEDCAMinContentionWindow.name: wsAPEDCAMinContentionWindow
wsAPEDCAMinContentionWindow.description: Specifies the upper limit of a range from which the initial random backoff wait time is determined. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 3 msec video(1) - 7 msec besteffort(2) - 15 msec background(3) - 15 msec

wsAPEDCAMaxContentionWindow.name: wsAPEDCAMaxContentionWindow
wsAPEDCAMaxContentionWindow.description: Specifies the upper limit for the doubling of the random backoff value, doubling continues until either the data frame is sent or this value is reached. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 7 msec video(1) - 15 msec besteffort(2) - 63 msec background(3) - 1023 msec

wsAPEDCAMaxBurst.name: wsAPEDCAMaxBurst
wsAPEDCAMaxBurst.description: Specifies the maximum burst length allowed for packet bursts on the wireless network. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 1500 micro sec video(1) - 3000 micro sec besteffort(2) - 0 micro sec background(3) - 0 micro sec

wsStationEDCAAIFS.name: wsStationEDCAAIFS
wsStationEDCAAIFS.description: Specifies the wait time for data frames. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 2 msec video(1) - 2 msec besteffort(2) - 3 msec background(3) - 7 msec

wsStationEDCAMinContentionWindow.name: wsStationEDCAMinContentionWindow
wsStationEDCAMinContentionWindow.description: Specifies the upper limit of a range from which the initial random backoff wait time is determined for station. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 3 msec video(1) - 7 msec besteffort(2) - 15 msec background(3) - 15 msec

wsStationEDCAMaxContentionWindow.name: wsStationEDCAMaxContentionWindow
wsStationEDCAMaxContentionWindow.description: Specifies the upper limit for the doubling of the random backoff value, doubling continues until either the data frame is sent or this value is reached. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 7 msec video(1) - 15 msec besteffort(2) - 63 msec background(3) - 1023 msec

wsStationEDCATXOPLimit.name: wsStationEDCATXOPLimit
wsStationEDCATXOPLimit.description: Specifies an interval of the time when a Wireless Multimedia Extensions(WME) client station has the right to initiate transmissions on to the wireless medium. The default values for each QOS Id is mentioned below: voice(0) - 47 msec video(1) - 94 msec besteffort(2) - 0 msec background(3) - 0 msec

wsNetworkTable.name: wsNetworkTable
wsNetworkTable.description: The following parameters can be configured for each network. A network may be assigned to one or more VAPs within an AP configuration profile. The first eight networks are created with default values, and cannot be deleted.

wsNetworkEntry.name: wsNetworkEntry
wsNetworkEntry.description: Each entry in this table is associated with a unique network Id.

wsNetworkId.name: wsNetworkId
wsNetworkId.description: Network Id used to uniquely identify the network.

wsNetworkIdRowStatus.name: wsNetworkIdRowStatus
wsNetworkIdRowStatus.description: Add Network ID to the network configuration table. The first 16 network configurations are created by default, they are applied to VAP-0 through VAP-15 in order on each radio when a new AP configuration profile is created (one default network configuration exists per VAP ID).

wsNetworkSSID.name: wsNetworkSSID
wsNetworkSSID.description: This object indicates Service Set ID specific to this Network. The first network is configured with a default SSID 'Guest Network', the rest of the networks have default SSIDs assigned based on the Network Id.

wsNetworkDefaultVLANId.name: wsNetworkDefaultVLANId
wsNetworkDefaultVLANId.description: Default VLAN Id assigned to the Network. The default VLAN is used if RADIUS based authentication is not configured for the network or the RADIUS server does not return a VLAN for a specific client.

wsNetworkHideSSIDMode.name: wsNetworkHideSSIDMode
wsNetworkHideSSIDMode.description: Flag to enable/disable inclusion of SSID in AP beacons.

wsNetworkDenyBcastMode.name: wsNetworkDenyBcastMode
wsNetworkDenyBcastMode.description: If client broadcasts probe requests to all available SSIDs this option controls whether or not the system will respond to the probe request. The 'disable' mode means that the system responds.

wsNetworkMACAuthenticationMode.name: wsNetworkMACAuthenticationMode
wsNetworkMACAuthenticationMode.description: This object indicates mode to disable, or enable and specify lookup method for authentication via client MAC address.

wsNetworkRadiusAccountingMode.name: wsNetworkRadiusAccountingMode
wsNetworkRadiusAccountingMode.description: Flag to enable/disable RADIUS accounting authentication for users on this network.

wsNetworkSecurityMode.name: wsNetworkSecurityMode
wsNetworkSecurityMode.description: Specifies authentication and encryption mode on this network.

wsNetworkWPAVersionsSupported.name: wsNetworkWPAVersionsSupported
wsNetworkWPAVersionsSupported.description: If Wi-Fi Protected Access(WPA) encryption mode is enabled, this object indicates the versions of WPA allowed by clients on this network.

wsNetworkWPACipherSuites.name: wsNetworkWPACipherSuites
wsNetworkWPACipherSuites.description: If WPA encryption mode is enabled, this object indicates which encryption solutions to use for WPA clients.

wsNetworkWPAKeyType.name: wsNetworkWPAKeyType
wsNetworkWPAKeyType.description: If WPA-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the type of the WPA key configured. Only ascii key type is supported for this release.

wsNetworkWPAKey.name: wsNetworkWPAKey
wsNetworkWPAKey.description: If WPA-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the pre-shared secret for WPA clients. For ASCII - 8-63 characters.

wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationMode.name: wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationMode
wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationMode.description: If WPA2 encryption is enabled, flag to enable/disable pre-authentication support for roaming WPA2 clients.

wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationLimit.name: wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationLimit
wsNetworkWPA2PreAuthenticationLimit.description: If WPA2 pre-authentication is enabled, this object specifies a limit on the number of APs within the peer group to which one client is allowed to be pre-authenticate.

wsNetworkWPA2RoambackKeyCacheHoldtime.name: wsNetworkWPA2RoambackKeyCacheHoldtime
wsNetworkWPA2RoambackKeyCacheHoldtime.description: Length of time in minutes a PMK will be cached by an AP after the client using this PMK has roamed away from this AP. Length of time a PMK will be cached by an AP after the PMK has been received from the WS. After this time has expired, the AP deletes the PMK entry from the security database.

wsNetworkStaticWEPAuthenticationMode.name: wsNetworkStaticWEPAuthenticationMode
wsNetworkStaticWEPAuthenticationMode.description: Indicates security configuration for static WEP.

wsNetworkUseWEPTransferKeyIndex.name: wsNetworkUseWEPTransferKeyIndex
wsNetworkUseWEPTransferKeyIndex.description: If wsNetSecurityMode is wepSharedKey, this object indicates which Wired Equivalent Privacy(WEP) algorithm network will use for encryption.

wsNetworkWEPKeyType.name: wsNetworkWEPKeyType
wsNetworkWEPKeyType.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the type WEP key configured.

wsNetworkWEPKeyLength.name: wsNetworkWEPKeyLength
wsNetworkWEPKeyLength.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies number of bits for the WEP key.

wsNetworkWEPKey1.name: wsNetworkWEPKey1
wsNetworkWEPKey1.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the key for WEP clients. Minimum characters required for key based on key type/length are: For ASCII/64 - 5 characters ASCII/128 - 13 characters HEX/64 - 10 characters HEX/128 - 26 characters

wsNetworkWEPKey2.name: wsNetworkWEPKey2
wsNetworkWEPKey2.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the key for WEP clients. Minimum characters required for key based on key type/length are: For ASCII/64 - 5 characters ASCII/128 - 13 characters HEX/64 - 10 characters HEX/128 - 26 characters

wsNetworkWEPKey3.name: wsNetworkWEPKey3
wsNetworkWEPKey3.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, specifies the key for WEP clients. Minimum characters required for key based on key type/length are: For ASCII/64 - 5 characters ASCII/128 - 13 characters HEX/64 - 10 characters HEX/128 - 26 characters

wsNetworkWEPKey4.name: wsNetworkWEPKey4
wsNetworkWEPKey4.description: If WEP-SharedKey security mode is enabled, this object specifies the key for WEP clients. Minimum characters required for key based on key type/length are: For ASCII/64 - 5 characters ASCII/128 - 13 characters HEX/64 - 10 characters HEX/128 - 26 characters

wsClearNetworkEntry.name: wsClearNetworkEntry
wsClearNetworkEntry.description: This is an action object. Setting this object to enable will set Network Id configuration to default configuration. Read on this object will always return disable.

wsNetworkRedirectMode.name: wsNetworkRedirectMode
wsNetworkRedirectMode.description: Specifies the redirect mode on this network.

wsNetworkRedirectURL.name: wsNetworkRedirectURL
wsNetworkRedirectURL.description: This object indicates HTTP Redirect URL on the Network Id.

wsIfNumber.name: wsIfNumber
wsIfNumber.description: A unique value to identify the wireless network interface.

wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerName.name: wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerName
wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerName.description: The name of the RADIUS server used for client authentications.

wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatu.name: wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatus
wsNetworkAuthRadiusServerConfiguredStatu.description: Indicates whether the specified named RADIUS Authentication server is configured in the RADIUS Client configuration.

wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerName.name: wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerName
wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerName.description: The name of the RADIUS server used for reporting wireless client associations and disassociations.

wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatu.name: wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatus
wsNetworkAcctRadiusServerConfiguredStatu.description: Indicates whether the specified named RADIUS Accounting server is configured in the RADIUS Client configuration.

wsUseNetworkRadiusConfig.name: wsUseNetworkRadiusConfig
wsUseNetworkRadiusConfig.description: This flag controls whether the VAP uses the network RADIUS configuration or global RADIUS configuration. When enabled, network RADIUS configuration shall be used.

wsNetworkDistTunnelMode.name: wsNetworkDistTunnelMode
wsNetworkDistTunnelMode.description: Flag to enable/disable Distributed Tunneling for this Network.

wsNetworkBcastKeyRefreshRate.name: wsNetworkBcastKeyRefreshRate
wsNetworkBcastKeyRefreshRate.description: The 802.1x broadcastkey refresh rate command specifies the interval after which the broadcast keys are changed.

wsNetworkSessionKeyRefreshRate.name: wsNetworkSessionKeyRefreshRate
wsNetworkSessionKeyRefreshRate.description: The 802.1x SessionKey refresh rate command specifies the interval after which the Unicast session keys are changed. This is applicable only dynamic WEP and WPA Enterprise modes.Valid values are 0 and from 30-86400.

wsNetworkARPSuppressionMode.name: wsNetworkARPSuppressionMode
wsNetworkARPSuppressionMode.description: Flag to enable/disable Wireless ARP Suppression for this Network.

wsNetworkBandSteerMode.name: wsNetworkBandSteerMode
wsNetworkBandSteerMode.description: Configure band steering on this VAP. To have band steering operationally enabled, the following conditions should be met: 1. SSIDs on both VAPs should match. 2. One radio should be in the 2.4-GHz band, and the other should be in the 5-GHz band.

wsNetworkClientQosTable.name: wsNetworkClientQosTable
wsNetworkClientQosTable.description: The following parameters can be configured for each network. This table extends the wsNetworkTable definition.

wsNetworkClientQosEntry.name: wsNetworkClientQosEntry
wsNetworkClientQosEntry.description: Each entry in this table is associated with a unique network ID, and defines its default client QoS parameters for a managed AP. These parameters are used for any wireless client on the designated network that does not have its own comparable parameter(s) defined via RADIUS when using 802.1X authentication.

wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitDown.name: wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitDown
wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitDown.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client for this network, thus controlling the maximum receive rate from the AP for a wireless client. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). This object may be set to any value in the range 0-4294967295. Any configured non-zero value is rounded down to the nearest 64000 bps by the AP, but no lower than 64000. Setting this object value to 0 disables bandwidth limiting in this direction.

wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.name: wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitUp
wsNetworkClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP for this network, thus controlling the maximum send rate to the AP for a wireless client. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). This object may be set to any value in the range 0-4294967295. Any configured non-zero value is rounded down to the nearest 64000 bps by the AP, but no lower than 64000. Setting this object value to 0 disables bandwidth limiting in this direction.

wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType.name: wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType
wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType.description: Access list type used for the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client for this network. Setting this object usually requires that the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownName object also be set at the same time (see the 'Object set restrictions' in that object's description for more information).

wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownName.name: wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownName
wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownName.description: Name of the access list to use in accordance with the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType as follows: none(1) - This object is not used and must not be set. ip(2) - This specifies an IP access list number in the range 1-199, entered as a character string rather than an integer, or an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid IP access list, as defined by the aclTable in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. mac(3) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid MAC access list name, as defined by the aclMacName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. ipv6(4) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid IPV6 access list name, as defined by the aclIpv6Name object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. Note that numbered IP access lists are specified here using a character string notation instead of an integer value. Object set restrictions: ------------------------ 1. When setting wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType to none(0), this object must not be set. 2. When setting wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType to any value other than none(0), both the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType and this object must be set at the same time (i.e. use multiple variable bindings). 3. This object may be set by itself in accordance with the existing wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlDownType value, provided the type value is anything other than none(0).

wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType.name: wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType
wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType.description: Access list type used for the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP for this network. Setting this object usually requires that the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpName object also be set at the same time (see the 'Object set restrictions' in that object's description for more information).

wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpName.name: wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpName
wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpName.description: Name of the access list to use in accordance with the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType as follows: none(1) - This object is not used and must not be set. ip(2) - This specifies an IP access list number in the range 1-199, entered as a character string rather than an integer, or an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid IP access list, as defined by the aclTable in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. mac(3) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid MAC access list name, as defined by the aclMacName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. ipv6(4) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid IPV6 access list name, as defined by the aclIpv6Name object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. Note that numbered IP access lists are specified here using a character string notation instead of an integer value. Object set restrictions: ------------------------ 1. When setting wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType to none(0), this object must not be set. 2. When setting wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType to any value other than none(0), both the wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType and this object must be set at the same time (i.e. use multiple variable bindings). 3. This object may be set by itself in accordance with the existing wsNetworkClientQosAccessControlUpType value, provided the type value is anything other than none(0).

wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType.name: wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType
wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType.description: DiffServ policy type used for the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client for this network. Setting this object usually requires that the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName object also be set at the same time (see the 'Object set restrictions' in that object's description for more information). Only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation.

wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName.name: wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName
wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName.description: Name of the DiffServ policy to use in accordance with the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType as follows: none(1) - This object is not used and must not be set. in(2) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid DiffServ policy name, as defined by the agentDiffServPolicyName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-DIFFSERV-PRIVATE-MIB. Note that only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation. Object set restrictions: ------------------------ 1. When setting wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType to none(0), this object must not be set. 2. When setting wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType to any value other than none(0), both the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType and this object must be set at the same time (i.e. use multiple variable bindings). 3. This object may be set by itself in accordance with the existing wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType value, provided the type value is anything other than none(0).

wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType.name: wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType
wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType.description: DiffServ policy type used for the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP for this network. Setting this object usually requires that the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName object also be set at the same time (see the 'Object set restrictions' in that object's description for more information). Only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation.

wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName.name: wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName
wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName.description: Name of the DiffServ policy to use in accordance with the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType as follows: none(1) - This object is not used and must not be set. in(2) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid DiffServ policy name, as defined by the agentDiffServPolicyName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-DIFFSERV-PRIVATE-MIB. Note that only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation. Object set restrictions: ------------------------ 1. When setting wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType to none(0), this object must not be set. 2. When setting wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType to any value other than none(0), both the wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType and this object must be set at the same time (i.e. use multiple variable bindings). 3. This object may be set by itself in accordance with the existing wsNetworkClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType value, provided the type value is anything other than none(0).

wsNetworkClientQosMode.name: wsNetworkClientQosMode
wsNetworkClientQosMode.description: Flag to enable/disable AP quality-of-service for wireless clients on this network.

wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsTable
wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsTable.description: This table represents the supported channels by AP Profile.

wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsEntry
wsAPProfileRadioSupportedChannelsEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a supported channel.

wsSupportedChannel.name: wsSupportedChannel
wsSupportedChannel.description: Indicates a channel currently supported by the radio for use with client connections. The set of supported channel numbers is determined by country code, radio mode, and in the case of modes that are compatible with 802.11n, primary channel selection and channel bandwidth settings.

wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsTable
wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsTable.description: This table represents the channels of an AP profile that are eligible for automatic channel selection.

wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsEntry
wsAPProfileRadioEligibleChannelsEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an eligible channel.

wsEligibleChannel.name: wsEligibleChannel
wsEligibleChannel.description: Indicates a channel currently eligible for automatic channel selection by the radio for use with client connections. The set of eligible channel numbers is a subset of the channels supported by the radio in its current configuration of country, mode, and in the case of modes that are compatible with 802.11n, primary channel selection and channel bandwidth settings.
