For 80Mhz 4 channels form a set and setting one channel would unset all the remaining channels in the set. Deleting one channel would unset all the channels in the set.

wsEligibleChannelRowStatus.name: wsEligibleChannelRowStatus
wsEligibleChannelRowStatus.description: The eligible channel status. Supported values: active(1) - valid instance createAndGo(4) - creates a new instance destroy(6) - removes an instance

wsAPProfileRadioTspecTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioTspecTable
wsAPProfileRadioTspecTable.description: This table contains TSPEC parameters that can be configured within an AP Profile per radio interface.

wsAPProfileRadioTspecEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioTspecEntry
wsAPProfileRadioTspecEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents TSPEC parameters that can be configured per radio interface within an AP profile. These entries augment the wsAPProfileRadioEntry definition for TSPEC configuration.

wsAPRadioTspecMode.name: wsAPRadioTspecMode
wsAPRadioTspecMode.description: The overall TSPEC operational mode for this radio. This object must be set to enable(1) for any of the other TSPEC ACM configuration parameters defined in this table row to have an effect. The default value for this object is disable(2).

wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmMode.name: wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmMode
wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmMode.description: Regulates mandatory admission control for the voice access category (AC). When set to enable(1), the voice AC may only be used by WMM-compliant client stations that have successfully established a TSPEC for this AC. Note that setting the wsAPRadioTspecLegacyWmmQueueMapMode object to enable(1) overrides the exclusive use of the voice AC by allowing legacy (i.e. non-WMM-compliant) client stations to use it as well.

wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmMode.name: wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmMode
wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmMode.description: Regulates mandatory admission control for the video access category (AC). When set to enable(1), the video AC may only be used by WMM-compliant client stations that have successfully established a TSPEC for this AC. Note that setting the wsAPRadioTspecLegacyWmmQueueMapMode object to enable(1) overrides the exclusive use of the video AC by allowing legacy (i.e. non-WMM-compliant) client stations to use it as well.

wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmLimit.name: wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmLimit
wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmLimit.description: Defines the maximum amount of wireless bandwidth utilization to admit for the voice access category. TSPEC requests that would cause this limit to be exceeded are rejected. Note that this value establishes an upper limit for wireless bandwidth to be admitted for this access category but does not guarantee that this limit can be reached. Setting this object value to 0 and the wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmMode object to enable(1) causes all TSPEC requests to be rejected by the AP for the voice access category. The sum of this value and the wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmLimit object value is not allowed to exceed 70. This value is treated as a percentage.

wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmLimit.name: wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmLimit
wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmLimit.description: Defines the maximum amount of wireless bandwidth utilization to admit for the video access category. TSPEC requests that would cause this limit to be exceeded are rejected. Note that this value establishes an upper limit for wireless bandwidth to be admitted for this access category but does not guarantee that this limit can be reached. Setting this object value to 0 and the wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmMode object to enable(1) causes all TSPEC requests to be rejected by the AP for the video access category. The sum of this value and the wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmLimit object value is not allowed to exceed 70. This value is treated as a percentage.

wsAPRadioTspecRoamReserveLimit.name: wsAPRadioTspecRoamReserveLimit
wsAPRadioTspecRoamReserveLimit.description: Defines the portion of the wsAPRadioTspecVoiceAcmLimit and wsAPRadioTspecVideoAcmLimit object values to hold in reserve for roaming clients only. If this value exceeds the current value in either of those two objects, respectively, then their entire ACM limit is used exclusively for roaming clients. Setting this object value to 0 causes none of the voice or video ACM limit values to be reserved for roaming clients - they compete equally with non-roaming clients for wireless network bandwidth. This value is treated as a percentage.

wsAPRadioTspecApInactivityTimeout.name: wsAPRadioTspecApInactivityTimeout
wsAPRadioTspecApInactivityTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time that an active traffic stream (TS) in the downlink direction may be idle, from the perspective of the AP, before it is deleted by the AP. For a bidirectional TS, both the wsAPRadioTspecApInactivityTimeout and the wsAPRadioTspecStaInactivityTimeout must expire in order for the TS to be deleted by the AP due to inactivity. If either of these timeouts is disabled, the AP will not delete a bidirectional TS due to inactivity. This value is specified in seconds. Setting this object value to 0 disables this timeout.

wsAPRadioTspecStaInactivityTimeout.name: wsAPRadioTspecStaInactivityTimeout
wsAPRadioTspecStaInactivityTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time that an active traffic stream (TS) in the uplink direction may be idle, from the perspective of the AP, before it is deleted by the AP. For a bidirectional TS, both the wsAPRadioTspecApInactivityTimeout and the wsAPRadioTspecStaInactivityTimeout must expire in order for the TS to be deleted by the AP due to inactivity. If either of these timeouts is disabled, the AP will not delete a bidirectional TS due to inactivity. This value is specified in seconds. Setting this object value to 0 disables this timeout.

wsAPRadioTspecLegacyWmmQueueMapMode.name: wsAPRadioTspecLegacyWmmQueueMapMode
wsAPRadioTspecLegacyWmmQueueMapMode.description: When enabled, the AP allows intermixing of legacy traffic with Wi-Fi Multimedia (WMM) traffic on access category queues that are operating according to admission control mandatory (ACM) rules. This mode is intended for use with non Wi-Fi Multimedia Enabled (non-WME) clients and is disabled by default. When this object is set to enable(1), both the voice and video access categories are accessible by wireless clients that do not have an admitted TSPEC, which can lead to underestimation of the available medium time by wireless TSPEC admission control. Use caution when enabling this mode and also consider using very small ACM limit values as well.

wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexTable.name: wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexTable
wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexTable.description: This table contains MCS indices that can be configured within an AP Profile per radio interface.

wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexEntry.name: wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexEntry
wsAPProfileRadioMCSIndexEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an MCS index that can be configured per radio interface within an AP profile.

wsAPRadioMCSIndexValue.name: wsAPRadioMCSIndexValue
wsAPRadioMCSIndexValue.description: Indicates an index value available for use with the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) for 802.11n connections. Not all radios support index values from 16 to 23.

wsAPRadioMCSIndexAvailable.name: wsAPRadioMCSIndexAvailable
wsAPRadioMCSIndexAvailable.description: Indicates that the associated index value has or has not been configured for use with the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) for 802.11n connections.

wsAPCodeDownloadServerIP.name: wsAPCodeDownloadServerIP
wsAPCodeDownloadServerIP.description: Indicates the server IP address to use for an AP code download request.

wsAPImageTypeFileTable.name: wsAPImageTypeFileTable
wsAPImageTypeFileTable.description: The AP image type capability table contain parameters that are configurable for each image type download.

wsAPImageTypeFileEntry.name: wsAPImageTypeFileEntry
wsAPImageTypeFileEntry.description: Each entry provides image type capability details for each AP image type supported by the WS.

wsAPImageFilePath.name: wsAPImageFilePath
wsAPImageFilePath.description: Indicates the file path on the server to use for an AP code download request.

wsAPImageFileName.name: wsAPImageFileName
wsAPImageFileName.description: Indicates file on the server to use for an AP code download request.

wsAPCodeDownloadMACAddress.name: wsAPCodeDownloadMACAddress
wsAPCodeDownloadMACAddress.description: Indicates an AP MAC address to use in a code download request for a single AP. MAC address zero indicates the code download request is for all managed APs. Setting this object initiates the code download. A read on this object always returns zero.

wsAPCodeDownloadGroupSize.name: wsAPCodeDownloadGroupSize
wsAPCodeDownloadGroupSize.description: Indicates the number of APs the wireless controller will issue a code download request to at one time.

wsAPCodeDownloadImageType.name: wsAPCodeDownloadImageType
wsAPCodeDownloadImageType.description: Indicates which image to download to the AP(s). Configurable values are: - tq3600, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq3600 code - image2, reserved future - image3, reserved future - tq2450, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq2450 code - tq4400, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq4400 code - tq4600, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq4600 code - tq3200, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq3200 code - tq3400, if download is for APs with hardware that only require tq3400 code - all, if download involves APs that require tq3600, tq2450, tq4400, tq4600, tq3200, and tq3400 code

wsAPCodeDownloadStatus.name: wsAPCodeDownloadStatus
wsAPCodeDownloadStatus.description: This indicates the current status for an AP code download request. Default value is not started.

wsAPCodeDownloadTotalCount.name: wsAPCodeDownloadTotalCount
wsAPCodeDownloadTotalCount.description: Indicates the number of WS managed APs at the time a code download request is started. Value is 1 if a download request is for single AP.

wsAPCodeDownloadSuccessCount.name: wsAPCodeDownloadSuccessCount
wsAPCodeDownloadSuccessCount.description: Indicates the total number of APs that have successfully completed code download.

wsAPCodeDownloadFailureCount.name: wsAPCodeDownloadFailureCount
wsAPCodeDownloadFailureCount.description: Indicates the total number of APs that have failed to complete a code download.

wsAPCodeDownloadAbortCount.name: wsAPCodeDownloadAbortCount
wsAPCodeDownloadAbortCount.description: Indicates the total number of APs aborted from the code download.

wsAPCodeDownloadAbort.name: wsAPCodeDownloadAbort
wsAPCodeDownloadAbort.description: Abort the current code download on managed AP(s). Supported values: disable(0) - Code download is not to be aborted. enable(1) - Code download is to be aborted.

wsChannelPlanTable.name: wsChannelPlanTable
wsChannelPlanTable.description: This table displays the channel plan parameters.

wsChannelPlanEntry.name: wsChannelPlanEntry
wsChannelPlanEntry.description: Each entry in this table will indicate the channel plan parameters for specific radio frequency.

wsChannelPlan.name: wsChannelPlan
wsChannelPlan.description: This object indicates the whether the channel plan is for ieee802dot11bORgn or ieee802dot11an.

wsChannelPlanMode.name: wsChannelPlanMode
wsChannelPlanMode.description: Indicates mode of computing and applying channel adjustments for managed AP radios operating in 2.4Ghz and 5Ghz band.

wsChannelPlanInterval.name: wsChannelPlanInterval
wsChannelPlanInterval.description: If channel plan mode is interval, this object indicates a regular interval in minutes at which to compute and apply a new channel adjustments.

wsChannelPlanTime.name: wsChannelPlanTime
wsChannelPlanTime.description: If channel plan mode is time, this object indicates the next scheduled time in minutes at which to compute and apply a new channel adjustments. Zero minutes stands for mid-night.

wsChannelPlanHistoryDepth.name: wsChannelPlanHistoryDepth
wsChannelPlanHistoryDepth.description: Indicates the maximum number of previously applied channel algorithm iterations stored on the controller and used in the next channel adjustment computation.

wsChannelPlanOperatingStatus.name: wsChannelPlanOperatingStatus
wsChannelPlanOperatingStatus.description: Indicates whether or not automatic channel adjustment is operating for managed AP radios operating in 2.4Ghz and 5Ghz band.

wsChannelPlanLastIterationStatus.name: wsChannelPlanLastIterationStatus
wsChannelPlanLastIterationStatus.description: Indicates the current iteration of channel plan adjustments for managed AP radio.

wsChannelPlanManualAction.name: wsChannelPlanManualAction
wsChannelPlanManualAction.description: This action object is used to: - Run the Proposed Channel Adjustment alogorithm - Abort the channel plan. - Clear the calculated 2.4Ghz and 5Ghz channel plan. Read on this object will always return none.

wsChannelPlanManualStatus.name: wsChannelPlanManualStatus
wsChannelPlanManualStatus.description: Indicates the current state of a manual request to compute or apply proposed channel adjustments.

wsChannelPlanLastAlgorithmTime.name: wsChannelPlanLastAlgorithmTime
wsChannelPlanLastAlgorithmTime.description: The time since the last channel plan algorithm ran.

wsChannelPlanChangeThreshold.name: wsChannelPlanChangeThreshold
wsChannelPlanChangeThreshold.description: The minimum signal strength (dBm) with which a neighbor must be detected on the current operational channel in order for the channel plan to consider moving away from the current channel.

wsChannelPlanChangeThresholdAdj.name: wsChannelPlanChangeThresholdAdj
wsChannelPlanChangeThresholdAdj.description: The number of dBm by which to reduce the Channel Change Threshold for detected managed APs based on the Transmit Power of the detected managed APs.

wsChannelPlanIgnoreUnamangedAPs.name: wsChannelPlanIgnoreUnamangedAPs
wsChannelPlanIgnoreUnamangedAPs.description: When enabled, the channel plan does not take into account the interfering unmanaged APs. Only managed APs are used for generating the channel plan.

wsChannelPlanRunOnManagedApFailure.name: wsChannelPlanRunOnManagedApFailure
wsChannelPlanRunOnManagedApFailure.description: When this administrative parameter is enabled, the controller runs ACA algorithm after it detects that a managed AP failed.

wsChannelPlanManagedAPFailureInterval.name: wsChannelPlanManagedAPFailureInterval
wsChannelPlanManagedAPFailureInterval.description: The number of seconds to wait before triggering the channel plan after a managed AP fails.

wsChannelPlanNumOfRadios.name: wsChannelPlanNumOfRadios
wsChannelPlanNumOfRadios.description: Number of radios operating in the band. This includes the radios with static channel assignment.

wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosAnalysed.name: wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosAnalysed
wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosAnalysed.description: Indicates the number of AP radios analyzed by the channel algorithm. This includes APs that operate on static channels.This value is reset at the start of each channel plan cycle.

wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosScanned.name: wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosScanned
wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosScanned.description: Indicates the number of AP radios for which a Channel Plan Request has been sent by the channel algorithm.This value is reset at the start of each channel plan cycle.

wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChanged.name: wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChanged
wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChanged.description: Indicates the number of AP radios whose operating channel changed. This includes APs whose channel is changed to the same channel as the original operating channel.This value is reset at the start of each channel plan cycle.

wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChangedToOrigCha.name: wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChangedToOrigChannel
wsChannelPlanNumOfRadiosChangedToOrigCha.description: Indicates the number of AP radios that scanned the candidate channels but ended on the same channel.This value is reset at the start of each channel plan cycle.

wsChannelPlanEstimatedTimeOfCompletion.name: wsChannelPlanEstimatedTimeOfCompletion
wsChannelPlanEstimatedTimeOfCompletion.description: The time for the estimated time of completion of the current channel plan cycle. When the channel plan is inactive the time stamp is zeroed out.

wsChannelPlanPercentageComplete.name: wsChannelPlanPercentageComplete
wsChannelPlanPercentageComplete.description: During the channel plan cycle this parameter is the percentage of the AP radios that have been analyzed. When the channel plan is inactive this value is 0.

wsChannelPlanHistoryTable.name: wsChannelPlanHistoryTable
wsChannelPlanHistoryTable.description: This table contains parameters related to channel plan algorithm history, each entry indicates a previously computed and applied channel adjustment for the specified iteration. The maximum number of channel adjustment iterations displayed is based on the 802.11b/g or 802.11a channel plan history depth.

wsChannelPlanHistoryEntry.name: wsChannelPlanHistoryEntry
wsChannelPlanHistoryEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents channel plan history for WS managed AP radio.

wsChannelPlanHistory.name: wsChannelPlanHistory
wsChannelPlanHistory.description: This object indicates the whether the channel adjustment is for 2.4Ghz or 5Ghz band.

wsChannelPlanAPMacAddress.name: wsChannelPlanAPMacAddress
wsChannelPlanAPMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of the AP.

wsManagedAPRadioTxPower.name: wsManagedAPRadioTxPower

wsManagedAPRadioAuthenticatedClients.name: wsManagedAPRadioAuthenticatedClients

wsManagedAPRadioWLANUtilization.name: wsManagedAPRadioWLANUtilization
wsManagedAPRadioWLANUtilization.description: Total network utilization for the physical radio. This value is based on radio statistics.

wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannelIndicator.description: This flag indicates if a fixed channel is configured and assigned to the radio.

wsManagedAPRadioMCAStatus.name: wsManagedAPRadioMCAStatus
wsManagedAPRadioMCAStatus.description: Indicates the current state of a manual request to change the channel on this radio.

wsManagedAPRadioFixedPowerIndicator.name: wsManagedAPRadioFixedPowerIndicator
wsManagedAPRadioFixedPowerIndicator.description: This flag indicates if a fixed power setting is configured and assigned to the radio.

wsManagedAPRadioMPAStatus.name: wsManagedAPRadioMPAStatus

wsManagedAPRadioNeighborCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioNeighborCount
wsManagedAPRadioNeighborCount.description: Total number of neighbors that can be seen by this radio in its RF area.

wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannelAction.name: wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannelAction
wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannelAction.description: This is an action object. When we set this object to apply, along with wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannel, controller starts applying fixed channel assignment for this radio. Read on this object will always return none.

wsManagedAPRadioFixedChannel.description: This object is used to assign the fixed channel for this radio on this Managed AP. wsManagedAPRadioFixedPowerAction.description: This is an action object. When we set this object to apply, controller starts applying fixed power adjustment for this radio. Read on this object will always return none.

wsManagedAPRadioFixedPower.name: wsManagedAPRadioFixedPower
wsManagedAPRadioFixedPower.description: This object is used to assign the fixed power for this radio on this Managed AP. wsManagedAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled.name: wsManagedAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled
wsManagedAPRadioResourceMeasEnabled.description: Current state of enablement for Radio Resource Management (RRM).

wsManagedAPRadioRetryCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioRetryCount
wsManagedAPRadioRetryCount.description: Number of times a MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retries.

wsManagedAPRadioMultipleRetryCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioMultipleRetryCount

wsManagedAPRadioFrameDuplicateCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioFrameDuplicateCount
wsManagedAPRadioFrameDuplicateCount.description: Number of times a frame is received and sequence control field indicates is a duplicate.

wsManagedAPRadioRTSSuccessCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioRTSSuccessCount
wsManagedAPRadioRTSSuccessCount.description: Count of CTS frames received in response to the RTS frames.

wsManagedAPRadioRTSFailureCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioRTSFailureCount
wsManagedAPRadioRTSFailureCount.description: Count of CTS frames not received in response to the RTS frames.

wsManagedAPRadioACKFailureCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioACKFailureCount
wsManagedAPRadioACKFailureCount.description: Count of ACK frames not received when expected.

wsManagedAPRadioRecvdFragmentCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioRecvdFragmentCount
wsManagedAPRadioRecvdFragmentCount.description: Count of successfully received MPDU frames of type data or management.

wsManagedAPRadioMcastRecvdFrameCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioMcastRecvdFrameCount
wsManagedAPRadioMcastRecvdFrameCount.description: Count of MSDU frames received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

wsManagedAPRadioFCSErrorCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioFCSErrorCount
wsManagedAPRadioFCSErrorCount.description: Count of FCS errors detected in a received MPDU frame.

wsManagedAPRadioTxFrameCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioTxFrameCount
wsManagedAPRadioTxFrameCount.description: Count of each successfully transmitted MSDU.

wsManagedAPRadioWEPUndecryptableCount.name: wsManagedAPRadioWEPUndecryptableCount
wsManagedAPRadioWEPUndecryptableCount.description: Count of encrypted frames received and the key configuration of the transmitter indicates that the frame should not have been encrypted or that frame was discarded due to the receiving station not implementing the privacy option.

wsManagedAPRadioWLANPktsRecvDropped.name: wsManagedAPRadioWLANPktsRecvDropped

wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesRecvDropped.name: wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesRecvDropped
wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesRecvDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction on this radio interface. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from AP to client.

wsManagedAPRadioWLANPktsTransmitDropped.name: wsManagedAPRadioWLANPktsTransmitDropped
wsManagedAPRadioWLANPktsTransmitDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction by this radio interface. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesTransmitDropped.name: wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesTransmitDropped
wsManagedAPRadioWLANBytesTransmitDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction by this radio interface. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsManagedAPNeighborAPListEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains neighbor AP information.

wsManagedAPNeighborClientListEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain neighbor client information.

wsNeighborClientMacAddress.description: The MAC address of neighbor client station.

wsNeighborClientRSSI.description: Indicates RSSI from neighbor clients on the radio.

wsNeighborClientAge.description: Indicates time since a client was last detected.

wsNeighborClientDiscoveryReason.name: wsNeighborClientDiscoveryReason
wsNeighborClientDiscoveryReason.description: Indicates discovery methods for the neighbor client.

wsManagedAPVAPStatusTable.description: This table contains status parameters for each VAP configured on a radio interface for a WS managed AP.

wsManagedAPVAPStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains status parameters of each VAP configured on radio.

wsManagedAPVAPStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain statistics available for each VAP on the WS managed AP.

wsManagedVAPAuthenticationFailures.description: Number of clients that have failed authentication to the VAP.

wsManagedVAPWLANPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted by an AP on this VAP.

wsManagedVAPWLANBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted by an AP on this VAP.

wsManagedVAPWLANBytesRecvDropped.name: wsManagedVAPWLANBytesRecvDropped

wsManagedVAPWLANBytesTransmitDropped.name: wsManagedVAPWLANBytesTransmitDropped
wsManagedVAPWLANBytesTransmitDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction by an AP on this VAP. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from client to AP.

wsManagedAPResetAll.description: This is an action object. Setting this object to enable will reset all the managed APs. Read on this object will always return disable.

wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListTable.name: wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListTable
wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListTable.description: This table represents eligible channel entries for an AP radio to consider for channel algorithm. It is based on country code, hardware capabilities and any configured channel limitations.

wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListEntry.name: wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListEntry
wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelListEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents eligible channel for an AP radio.

wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannel.name: wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannel
wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannel.description: Indicates list of supported channel by the managed ap. List contains one or more entries from 1-255, actual range is determined by physical mode and country code.

wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelRdrDetReq.name: wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelRdrDetRequired
wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelRdrDetReq.description: This flag indicates if radar detection is enabled or not on this channel.

wsManagedAPRadioEligibleChannelRdrDetect.description: This flag indicates if radar is detected or not on this channel.

wsAssociatedClientStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain client status parameters assocaited with the WS managed AP.

wsAssociatedClientTunnelIpAddress.name: wsAssociatedClientTunnelIpAddress
wsAssociatedClientTunnelIpAddress.description: Indicates network IP address of the client station, 0.0.0.0 indicates unknown. Tunnel IP subnet is present only for clients authenticated with tunneled VAPs.

wsAssociatedClientUserName.name: wsAssociatedClientUserName
wsAssociatedClientUserName.description: Indicates user name of the client that have authenticated via 802.1x, clients on networks with other security modes will not have a user name.

wsAssociatedClientSSID.name: wsAssociatedClientSSID
wsAssociatedClientSSID.description: Indicates the network on which the client is connected.

wsAssociatedClientVLAN.name: wsAssociatedClientVLAN
wsAssociatedClientVLAN.description: If client is on VAP using VLAN data forwarding mode, indicates obsolete assigned VLAN.

wsAssociatedClientTxDataRate.name: wsAssociatedClientTxDataRate
wsAssociatedClientTxDataRate.description: Indicates the data rate, AP will actually support in setting up communications with client stations represented by a count from 2 - 1200, corresponding to data rates in multiples of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 600 Mbit/s. Supported Data Rate Mbps 2 1 4 2 11 5.5 12 6 18 9 and so on.

wsAssociatedClientInactivePeriod.name: wsAssociatedClientInactivePeriod
wsAssociatedClientInactivePeriod.description: For a current association, period of time that the AP has not seen any traffic for the client.

wsAssociatedClientDisassociateAction.name: wsAssociatedClientDisassociateAction
wsAssociatedClientDisassociateAction.description: This is an action object. Setting this object to start will initiate the disassociation of associated client. Read on this object will always return none.

wsAssociatedClientAge.name: wsAssociatedClientAge
wsAssociatedClientAge.description: Indicates time since the controller has received new data for this client.

wsAssociatedClientAssociatingSwitch.name: wsAssociatedClientAssociatingSwitch
wsAssociatedClientAssociatingSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the client is associated to an AP managed by this controller or peer-controller.

wsAssociatedClientSwitchMacAddress.name: wsAssociatedClientSwitchMacAddress
wsAssociatedClientSwitchMacAddress.description: MAC address of the WS associating the client.

wsAssociatedClientSwitchIpAddress.name: wsAssociatedClientSwitchIpAddress
wsAssociatedClientSwitchIpAddress.description: IP address of the WS associating the client.

wsAssociatedClientDot11nCapable.name: wsAssociatedClientDot11nCapable
wsAssociatedClientDot11nCapable.description: Flag indicating whether this client is capable of 802.11n operation.

wsAssociatedClientStbcCapable.name: wsAssociatedClientStbcCapable
wsAssociatedClientStbcCapable.description: Flag indicating whether this client is capable of Space Time Block Code (STBC) operation.

wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelStatus.name: wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelStatus
wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelStatus.description: Indicates whether L2 Distributed Tunneling is Enabled or Disabled

wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatus.name: wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatus
wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatus.description: Indicates whether the client is using the distrubuted tunnel or not. Also indicates if it is a roamed client or not.

wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac.name: wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac
wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac.description: Indicates MAC Address of the client's Home AP. Here the client should be associated with the network on which the L2 Distributed Tunneling is enabled.

wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMac.name: wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMac
wsAssociatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMac.description: MAC Address of the client's Association AP to which the client has roamed to.

wsAssociatedClientChannel.description: Indicates channel for associated client entry.

wsAssociatedClientNwTime.name: wsAssociatedClientNwTime
wsAssociatedClientNwTime.description: Indicates time since this client first authenticated with the network.

wsAssociatedClientIpAddress.name: wsAssociatedClientIpAddress
wsAssociatedClientIpAddress.description: Indicates network IPv4 address of the client station detetecd through ARP snooping, 0.0.0.0 indicates unknown.

wsAssociatedClientRRMSupported.name: wsAssociatedClientRRMSupported
wsAssociatedClientRRMSupported.description: Indicates if the Radio Resource Management (RRM) portion of the IEEE 802.11k standard is supported by client and RRM is enabled is on the AP Profile. Value 2 indicates the client supports RRM portion and RRM Mode is not enabled on AP Profile. Value 3 indicates client doesnot support RRM

wsAssociatedClientRRMLocationReportSuppo.name: wsAssociatedClientRRMLocationReportSupported
wsAssociatedClientRRMLocationReportSuppo.description: Indicates if the client can support RRM location report requests.

wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconTableMeasurem.name: wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconTableMeasurementSupported

wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconActiveMeasure.description: Indicates if the client supports active scan capability.

wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMeasur.name: wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMeasurementSupported
wsAssociatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMeasur.description: Indicates if the client supports passive scan capability.

wsAssociatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasurem.name: wsAssociatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasurementSupported
wsAssociatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasurem.description: Indicates if the client supports RRM channel load measurement.

wsAssociatedClientStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain statistics available for each client associated a WS managed AP.

wsAssociatedClientPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received by a managed AP from the client station.

wsAssociatedClientBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received by a managed AP from the client station.

wsAssociatedClientPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted by a managed AP to the client station.

wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitted.name: wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitted
wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted by a managed AP to the client station.

wsAssociatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd.name: wsAssociatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd
wsAssociatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd.description: Total duplicate packets received from the client station.

wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd.name: wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd
wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd.description: Total fragmented packets received from the client station.

wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsTransmit.name: wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsTransmitted
wsAssociatedClientFragmentedPktsTransmit.description: Total fragmented packets transmitted to the client station.

wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryCount.name: wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryCount
wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryCount.description: Indicates number of times transmits to client station succeeded after one or more retries.

wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryFailedCou.name: wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryFailedCount
wsAssociatedClientTransmitRetryFailedCou.description: Number of times transmits to client station failed after one or more retries.

wsAssociatedClientBytesRecvDropped.name: wsAssociatedClientBytesRecvDropped
wsAssociatedClientBytesRecvDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction by a managed AP from the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP.

wsAssociatedClientPktsTransmitDropped.name: wsAssociatedClientPktsTransmitDropped
wsAssociatedClientPktsTransmitDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction by a managed AP to the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitDropped.name: wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitDropped
wsAssociatedClientBytesTransmitDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction by a managed AP to the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAssociatedClientTsViolatePktsRecvd.name: wsAssociatedClientTsViolatePktsRecvd

wsAssociatedClientNeighborManagedAPStatu.description: Each entry in this table contain WS managed APs that can be seen by client in its RF area.

wsSwitchAssociatedClientMacAddress.name: wsSwitchAssociatedClientMacAddress
wsSwitchAssociatedClientMacAddress.description: Ethernet address of the associated client station.

wsAssociatedClientQosStatusEntry.name: wsAssociatedClientQosStatusEntry
wsAssociatedClientQosStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains client QoS status parameters for a client associated with the WS managed AP.

wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDown.name: wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDown
wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDown.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client, thus controlling the maximum receive rate from the AP for this wireless client. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). The displayed value represents the actual bandwidth rate in use for the client, which may differ from the configured value since the AP rounds down to the nearest 64000 bps. A value of 0 indicates bandwidth limiting is disabled in this direction for the client.

wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.name: wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp
wsAssociatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP, thus controlling the maximum send rate from this wireless client to the AP. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). The displayed value represents the actual bandwidth rate in use for the client, which may differ from the configured value since the AP rounds down to the nearest 64000 bps. A value of 0 indicates bandwidth limiting is disabled in this direction for the client.

wsAssociatedClientSessionPktsRecvd.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionPktsRecvd

wsAssociatedClientSessionBytesRecvd.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionBytesRecvd

wsAssociatedClientSessionPktsTransmitted.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionPktsTransmitted

wsAssociatedClientSessionFragmentedPktsT.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionFragmentedPktsTransmitted

wsAssociatedClientSessionBytesTransmitDr.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionBytesTransmitDropped
wsAssociatedClientSessionBytesTransmitDr.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction by managed APs to the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAssociatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsRe.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsRecvd
wsAssociatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsRe.description: Number of packets received by managed APs from a client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session that are in excess of the client's alotted traffic stream (TS) uplink bandwidth, or are for an access category requiring admission control to which the client station has not been admitted.

wsAssociatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsTr.name: wsAssociatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsTransmitted

wsAssociatedClientQosCachedStatusTable.name: wsAssociatedClientQosCachedStatusTable

wsPeerStatusTable.name: wsPeerStatusTable
wsPeerStatusTable.description: This table contain status parameters of peer controllers of wireless controller.

wsPeerStatusEntry.name: wsPeerStatusEntry
wsPeerStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the status parameters of each peer of wireless controller.

wsPeerIpAddress.name: wsPeerIpAddress
wsPeerIpAddress.description: IP address of the peer controller.

wsPeerClusterControllerIndicator.name: wsPeerClusterControllerIndicator
wsPeerClusterControllerIndicator.description: Indicates if the peer controller is currently the Cluster Controller of the peer group or not.

wsPeerTotalPeerSwitches.name: wsPeerTotalPeerSwitches
wsPeerTotalPeerSwitches.description: Total number of peer controllers detected on the network.

wsPeerVendorId.name: wsPeerVendorId
wsPeerVendorId.description: Indicates vendor of peer controller software.

wsPeerProtocolVersion.name: wsPeerProtocolVersion
wsPeerProtocolVersion.description: Indicates software version of peer controller.

wsPeerSoftwareVersion.name: wsPeerSoftwareVersion
wsPeerSoftwareVersion.description: Indicates the protocol version of software on the peer controller.

wsPeerDiscoveryReason.name: wsPeerDiscoveryReason
wsPeerDiscoveryReason.description: Indicates the discovery method of peer controller.

wsPeerAge.name: wsPeerAge
wsPeerAge.description: Indicates time in seconds since last communication with the controller.

wsPeerManagedAPCount.name: wsPeerManagedAPCount
wsPeerManagedAPCount.description: Number of APs in the peer managed AP database that are authenticated, configured, and have an active connection with the wireless controller.

wsPeerConfigRequestAction.name: wsPeerConfigRequestAction
wsPeerConfigRequestAction.description: This action object is used to: - start - Start the config push into the peer controller. - Read on this object will always return none.

wsPeerConfigRequestStatus.name: wsPeerConfigRequestStatus
wsPeerConfigRequestStatus.description: The status for the configuration push operation to this peer controller.

wsPeerConfigSwitchIp.name: wsPeerConfigSwitchIp
wsPeerConfigSwitchIp.description: IP Address of the last controller from which this controller received any wireless configuration data.

wsPeerConfigReceived.name: wsPeerConfigReceived
wsPeerConfigReceived.description: Indicates which portions of configuration were last received from a peer controller. The combination of configurations are denoted by doing 'AND' of the values.BIT zero is ignored. Ex: Value 9 specifies only bit 2 and 5 are set, So it denotes channelPowerConfig and globalConfig received

wsPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp.name: wsPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp
wsPeerConfigReceivedTimestamp.description: The last time this controller received any configuration data from a peer controller.

wsPeerSwitchManagedAPTable.name: wsPeerSwitchManagedAPTable
wsPeerSwitchManagedAPTable.description: This table contain Managed AP database of the peer controllers of wireless controller.

wsPeerSwitchManagedAPEntry.name: wsPeerSwitchManagedAPEntry
wsPeerSwitchManagedAPEntry.description: Each entry describes the Managed AP Entry of the peer of wireless controller.

wsPeerSwitchIpAddress.name: wsPeerSwitchIpAddress
wsPeerSwitchIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Peer controller.

wsPeerSwitchAPMacAddress.name: wsPeerSwitchAPMacAddress
wsPeerSwitchAPMacAddress.description: The VAP0 MAC address of the AP managed by the peer controller.

wsPeerSwitchAPLocation.name: wsPeerSwitchAPLocation
wsPeerSwitchAPLocation.description: This object indicates descriptive location of the managed AP by the peer controller.

wsPeerSwitchAPIPAddress.name: wsPeerSwitchAPIPAddress
wsPeerSwitchAPIPAddress.description: IP address for the peer managed AP.

wsPeerSwitchAPProfileId.name: wsPeerSwitchAPProfileId
wsPeerSwitchAPProfileId.description: Unique ID for the peer managed AP's configuration profile.

wsPeerSwitchAPProfileName.name: wsPeerSwitchAPProfileName
wsPeerSwitchAPProfileName.description: The descriptive name for the peer managed AP's configuration profile.

wsPeerSwitchAPHardwareType.name: wsPeerSwitchAPHardwareType
wsPeerSwitchAPHardwareType.description: The Hardware platform for the AP. 1 --> BROADCOM.

wsRFScanAPStatusTable.name: wsRFScanAPStatusTable
wsRFScanAPStatusTable.description: This table is maintained with RF scan data received from the WS managed APs.

wsRFScanAPStatusEntry.name: wsRFScanAPStatusEntry
wsRFScanAPStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain RF scan data received from the WS managed AP.

wsRFScanAPMacAddress.name: wsRFScanAPMacAddress
wsRFScanAPMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the detected AP, this could be a physical radio interface or VAP MAC.

wsRFScanAPRadioInterface.name: wsRFScanAPRadioInterface
wsRFScanAPRadioInterface.description: If status indicates a managed AP, this indicates the radio interface on the Detected AP, if the value is unknown (i.e. Rogue or third party APs) it is set to '0'.

wsRFScanAPBaseMacAddress.name: wsRFScanAPBaseMacAddress
wsRFScanAPBaseMacAddress.description: If status indicates a managed AP, this indicates the base MAC address of the detected AP, If the value is unknown (i.e. Rogue of third party AP's) it is set to '0'.

wsRFScanAPSSID.name: wsRFScanAPSSID
wsRFScanAPSSID.description: Service Set Id of the detected network.

wsRFScanAPPhysicalMode.name: wsRFScanAPPhysicalMode
wsRFScanAPPhysicalMode.description: Indicates the 802.11 mode being used on an AP.

wsRFScanAPChannel.name: wsRFScanAPChannel
wsRFScanAPChannel.description: Indicates transmit channel of an AP.

wsRFScanAPTxRate.name: wsRFScanAPTxRate
wsRFScanAPTxRate.description: Indicates the rate at which an AP is currently transmitting data, from 1 Mbit/s to 600 Mbit/s.

wsRFScanAPBeaconInterval.name: wsRFScanAPBeaconInterval
wsRFScanAPBeaconInterval.description: Indicates beacon interval for a neighbor AP network.

wsRFScanAPStatus.name: wsRFScanAPStatus
wsRFScanAPStatus.description: Indicates the managed status of an AP.

wsRFScanAPDiscoveredAge.name: wsRFScanAPDiscoveredAge
wsRFScanAPDiscoveredAge.description: Indicates timestamp in seconds when an AP was first detected.

wsRFScanAPAge.name: wsRFScanAPAge
wsRFScanAPAge.description: Indicates time in seconds since an AP was last detected in the scan.

wsRFScanAPStatusInitial.name: wsRFScanAPStatusInitial
wsRFScanAPStatusInitial.description: Indicates the initial status of an AP.

wsRFScanAPSecurityMode.name: wsRFScanAPSecurityMode
wsRFScanAPSecurityMode.description: Indicates the security mode of an AP.

wsRFScanAPHighRate.name: wsRFScanAPHighRate
wsRFScanAPHighRate.description: Indicates the highest supported rate advertised by an AP in Mbps.

wsRFScanAPDot11nMode.name: wsRFScanAPDot11nMode
wsRFScanAPDot11nMode.description: Indicates whether 802.11n is supported by an AP.

wsRFScanAPAdHoc.name: wsRFScanAPAdHoc
wsRFScanAPAdHoc.description: Indicates that the beacon frame was received from an ad hoc network for an AP.

wsRFScanAPPeerManaged.name: wsRFScanAPPeerManaged
wsRFScanAPPeerManaged.description: Indicates that an AP is managed by a peer controller.

wsRFScanAPRogueMitigation.name: wsRFScanAPRogueMitigation
wsRFScanAPRogueMitigation.description: Indicates whether rogue AP mitigation is in progress for an AP.

wsRFScanAPAcknowledgeRogue.name: wsRFScanAPAcknowledgeRogue
wsRFScanAPAcknowledgeRogue.description: This is a command that allows the administrator to restore the initial status for this AP in the RF Scan database. Read on this object will always return no-action.

wsRFScanAPRRMSupported.name: wsRFScanAPRRMSupported
wsRFScanAPRRMSupported.description: Advertised status of Radio Resource Management (RRM) capability.

wsRFScanAPDot11acMode.name: wsRFScanAPDot11acMode
wsRFScanAPDot11acMode.description: Indicates whether 802.11ac is supported by an AP.

wsRFScanAPEntriesPurge.name: wsRFScanAPEntriesPurge
wsRFScanAPEntriesPurge.description: This is an action object used to purge the RF scan entries present in the network. Read on this object will always return disable.

wsFailureAPStatusTable.name: wsFailureAPStatusTable
wsFailureAPStatusTable.description: This table contain status parameters of APs that failed to authenticate, or associate with wireless controller.

wsFailureAPStatusEntry.name: wsFailureAPStatusEntry
wsFailureAPStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain status parameters of failed AP.

wsFailedAPMacAddress.name: wsFailedAPMacAddress
wsFailedAPMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of the failed AP.

wsFailedAPIpAddress.name: wsFailedAPIpAddress
wsFailedAPIpAddress.description: The network IP address of the failed AP.

wsFailedAPVendorId.name: wsFailedAPVendorId
wsFailedAPVendorId.description: Indicates vendor of the failed AP.

wsFailedAPSoftwareVersion.name: wsFailedAPSoftwareVersion
wsFailedAPSoftwareVersion.description: Indicates software version of the failed AP.

wsFailedAPHWType.name: wsFailedAPHWType
wsFailedAPHWType.description: Indicates hardware type of the failed AP.

wsFailedAPFailureType.name: wsFailedAPFailureType
wsFailedAPFailureType.description: Indicates the last type of failure that occured.

wsFailedAPValidationFailureCount.name: wsFailedAPValidationFailureCount
wsFailedAPValidationFailureCount.description: Number of times the AP failed to authenticate due to MAC address validation failure.

wsFailedAPAuthenticationFailureCount.name: wsFailedAPAuthenticationFailureCount
wsFailedAPAuthenticationFailureCount.description: Number of times the AP failed to authenticate due to incorrect authentication credentials.

wsFailedAPProtocolVersion.name: wsFailedAPProtocolVersion
wsFailedAPProtocolVersion.description: Indicates the protocol version supported by the software on this AP.

wsFailedAPReportingSwitch.name: wsFailedAPReportingSwitch
wsFailedAPReportingSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the AP failure happened on this controller or on the peer-controller.

wsFailedAPSwitchMacAddress.name: wsFailedAPSwitchMacAddress
wsFailedAPSwitchMacAddress.description: MAC address of the WS reporting the AP Authentication Failure.

wsFailedAPSwitchIpAddress.name: wsFailedAPSwitchIpAddress
wsFailedAPSwitchIpAddress.description: IP address of the WS reporting the AP Authentication Failure.

wsAPFailureEntriesPurge.name: wsAPFailureEntriesPurge
wsAPFailureEntriesPurge.description: This is an action object used to purge the failed AP entries. Read on this object will always return disable.

wsAdHocClientStatusTable.name: wsAdHocClientStatusTable
wsAdHocClientStatusTable.description: This table contains information related to Ad hoc clients detected in the network.

wsAdHocClientStatusEntry.name: wsAdHocClientStatusEntry
wsAdHocClientStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents Ad hoc client detected in the network.

wsAdHocClientMacAddress.name: wsAdHocClientMacAddress
wsAdHocClientMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of the Ad hoc client detected. wsDetectedAPMacAddress.name: wsDetectedAPMacAddress
wsDetectedAPMacAddress.description: The MAC address of an AP which last detected the Ad hoc client.

wsDetectedAPRadioInterface.name: wsDetectedAPRadioInterface
wsDetectedAPRadioInterface.description: The radio interface of an AP which last detected the Ad hoc client.

wsAdHocClientDetectionMode.name: wsAdHocClientDetectionMode
wsAdHocClientDetectionMode.description: The mechanism through which this Ad hoc device is detected. This can be through beacon frame or data frame.

wsAdHocClientAge.name: wsAdHocClientAge

wsAdHocClientEntriesPurge.name: wsAdHocClientEntriesPurge

wsDetectedClientStatus.description: This object indicates client's status. wsDetectedClientThreatMitigationStatus.description: This object indicates whether threat mitigation has been done for this client.

wsAPStateTrapMode.description: Flag to enable/disable SNMP traps for: WS Managed AP Discovered, WS Managed AP Failed, WS Managed AP Unknown Protocol Discovered.

wsAPFailureTrapMode.name: wsAPFailureTrapMode
wsAPFailureTrapMode.description: Flag to enable/disable SNMP traps for: WS AP Association Failure, WS AP Authentication Failure.

wsRogueAPTrapMode.name: wsRogueAPTrapMode

wsRFScanTrapMode.name: wsRFScanTrapMode

wsModeEnabled.description: A wsModeEnabled trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that Wireless functionality on the device is enabled.

wsModeDisabled.name: wsModeDisabled
wsModeDisabled.description: A wsModeDisabled trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that Wireless functionality on the device is disabled.

wsManagedAPDatabaseFull.name: wsManagedAPDatabaseFull
wsManagedAPDatabaseFull.description: A wsAPDatabaseFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that AP Database is full.

wsManagedAPNeighborAPListFull.name: wsManagedAPNeighborAPListFull
wsManagedAPNeighborAPListFull.description: A wsManagedAPNeighborListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that ManagedAP neighbor AP list is full.

wsManagedAPNeighborClientListFull.name: wsManagedAPNeighborClientListFull
wsManagedAPNeighborClientListFull.description: A wsManagedAPNeighborClientListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that ManagedAP neighbor client list is full.

wsAPFailureListFull.name: wsAPFailureListFull
wsAPFailureListFull.description: A wsAPFailureListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that AP failure list full.

wsRFScanAPListFull.name: wsRFScanAPListFull
wsRFScanAPListFull.description: A wsRFScanAPListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that RF scan AP list is full.

wsClientAssociationDatabaseFull.name: wsClientAssociationDatabaseFull
wsClientAssociationDatabaseFull.description: A wsClientAssociationDatabaseFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that client association database is full.

wsPeerSwitchDiscovered.name: wsPeerSwitchDiscovered
wsPeerSwitchDiscovered.description: A wsPeerSwitchDiscovered trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected peer controller in the network.

wsPeerSwitchFailed.name: wsPeerSwitchFailed
wsPeerSwitchFailed.description: A wsPeerSwitchFailed trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that peer controller connection failed.

wsPeerSwitchUnknownProtocol.name: wsPeerSwitchUnknownProtocol
wsPeerSwitchUnknownProtocol.description: A wsPeerSwitchUnknownProtocol trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected unknown protocol between wireless controller and peer controller communication.

wsManagedAPDiscovered.name: wsManagedAPDiscovered
wsManagedAPDiscovered.description: A wsManagedAPDiscovered trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the managed AP.

wsManagedAPFailed.name: wsManagedAPFailed
wsManagedAPFailed.description: A wsManagedAPFailed trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the failed AP.

wsManagedAPUnknownProtocol.name: wsManagedAPUnknownProtocol
wsManagedAPUnknownProtocol.description: A wsManagedAPUnknownProtocol trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected the unknown protocol between wireless controller and managed AP communication.

wsAPAssociationFailure.name: wsAPAssociationFailure
wsAPAssociationFailure.description: A wsAPAssociationFailure trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that AP association failed.

wsAPAuthenticationFailure.name: wsAPAuthenticationFailure
wsAPAuthenticationFailure.description: A wsAPAuthenticationFailure trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that AP authentication failed.

wsRFScanRogueAPDetected.name: wsRFScanRogueAPDetected
wsRFScanRogueAPDetected.description: A wsRFScanRogueAPDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected Rogue AP through RF Scan.

wsRFScanAPDetected.name: wsRFScanAPDetected
wsRFScanAPDetected.description: A wsRFScanAPDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected AP through RF Scan.

wsRFScanNewClientDetected.name: wsRFScanNewClientDetected
wsRFScanNewClientDetected.description: A wsRFScanNewClientDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected new client through RF Scan.

wsClientAssociationDetected.name: wsClientAssociationDetected
wsClientAssociationDetected.description: A wsClientAssociationDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected client association.

wsClientDisassociationDetected.name: wsClientDisassociationDetected
wsClientDisassociationDetected.description: A wsClientDisassociationDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected client disassociation.

wsClientRoamDetected.name: wsClientRoamDetected
wsClientRoamDetected.description: A wsClientRoamDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected client roaming.

wsClientAssociationFailure.name: wsClientAssociationFailure
wsClientAssociationFailure.description: A wsClientAssociationFailure trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected client association failure.

wsClientAuthenticationFailure.name: wsClientAuthenticationFailure
wsClientAuthenticationFailure.description: A wsAuthenticationFailure trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected client authentication failure.

wsAdHocClientDetected.name: wsAdHocClientDetected
wsAdHocClientDetected.description: A wsAdHocClientDetected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected Ad hoc client.

wsWLANBandwidthUtilizationExceeded.name: wsWLANBandwidthUtilizationExceeded
wsWLANBandwidthUtilizationExceeded.description: A wsWLANBandwidthUtilizationExceeded trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected WLAN bandwidth utilization exceeding the limit.

wsAdHocClientListFull.name: wsAdHocClientListFull
wsAdHocClientListFull.description: A wsAdHocClientListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that Ad hoc client database is full.

wsPeerSwitchConfigurationCommandReceived.name: wsPeerSwitchConfigurationCommandReceived
wsPeerSwitchConfigurationCommandReceived.description: A wsPeerSwitchConfigurationCommandReceived trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has received Configuration command from the peer controller in the network. The config mask received is also returned in the trap.

wsPeerSwitchManagedAPLimitExceeded.name: wsPeerSwitchManagedAPLimitExceeded
wsPeerSwitchManagedAPLimitExceeded.description: A wsPeerSwitchManagedAPLimitExceeded trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the Peer controller Managed AP database limit has exceeded.

wsPeerSwitchClientLimitExceeded.name: wsPeerSwitchClientLimitExceeded
wsPeerSwitchClientLimitExceeded.description: A wsPeerSwitchClientLimitExceeded trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the Peer controller Client database limit has exceeded.

wsClusterControllerElected.name: wsClusterControllerElected
wsClusterControllerElected.description: A wsClusterControllerElected trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has elected itself as Cluster Controller in the peer group.

wsClusterMaxAPExceeded.name: wsClusterMaxAPExceeded
wsClusterMaxAPExceeded.description: A wsClusterMaxAPExceeded trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the managed APs in the network has exceeded.

wsRoguesPresent.name: wsRoguesPresent
wsRoguesPresent.description: A wsRoguesPresent trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected one or more Rogues present in the network.

wsDetectedClientListFull.name: wsDetectedClientListFull
wsDetectedClientListFull.description: A wsDetectedClientListFull trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that Detected client database is full.

wsRogueClientsPresent.name: wsRogueClientsPresent
wsRogueClientsPresent.description: A wsRogueClientsPresent trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected one or more Rogue Clients present in the network.

wsChannelPlanAlgoComplete.name: wsChannelPlanAlgoComplete
wsChannelPlanAlgoComplete.description: A wsChannelAlgorithmComplete trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected channel algorithm complete event.

wsPowerPlanAlgoComplete.name: wsPowerPlanAlgoComplete
wsPowerPlanAlgoComplete.description: A wsPowerAlgorithmComplete trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected power algorithm complete event.

wsLocallyManagedAPLimitExceeded.name: wsLocallyManagedAPLimitExceeded
wsLocallyManagedAPLimitExceeded.description: A wsLocallyManagedAPLimitExceeded trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the WS locally managed AP limit is exceeded.

wsTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams.name: wsTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams
wsTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams.description: Total number of traffic streams currently established for the voice access category. For a Cluster Controller, this value represents the entire cluster.

wsTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams.name: wsTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams
wsTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams.description: Total number of traffic streams currently established for the video access category. For a Cluster Controller, this value represents the entire cluster.

wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients.name: wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients
wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients.description: Total number of clients that currently possess one or more traffic streams in any access category. For a Cluster Controller, this value represents the entire cluster.

wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingClients.name: wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingClients
wsTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingClients.description: Total number of roaming clients that currently possess one or more traffic streams in any access category. For a Cluster Controller, this value represents the entire cluster.

wsGlobalTspecStatisticsTable.name: wsGlobalTspecStatisticsTable
wsGlobalTspecStatisticsTable.description: This table contains global TSPEC statistics indexed on a per access category (AC) basis.

wsGlobalTspecStatisticsEntry.name: wsGlobalTspecStatisticsEntry
wsGlobalTspecStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry contains global TSPEC statistics indexed on a per access category (AC) basis for the wireless controller. If this controller is a Cluster Controller, these object values represent the entire cluster.

wsTspecACIndex.name: wsTspecACIndex
wsTspecACIndex.description: Access category (AC) index used for referencing objects in the table row. Only those ACs that support mandatory admission control are available through this index. The currently supported AC index values are: 0 - Voice 1 - Video

wsTotalWLANTspecPktsRecvd.name: wsTotalWLANTspecPktsRecvd
wsTotalWLANTspecPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANTspecPktsTransmitted.name: wsTotalWLANTspecPktsTransmitted
wsTotalWLANTspecPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANTspecBytesRecvd.name: wsTotalWLANTspecBytesRecvd
wsTotalWLANTspecBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANTspecBytesTransmitted.name: wsTotalWLANTspecBytesTransmitted
wsTotalWLANTspecBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANTspecsAccepted.name: wsTotalWLANTspecsAccepted
wsTotalWLANTspecsAccepted.description: Total number of TSPECs accepted across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANTspecsRejected.name: wsTotalWLANTspecsRejected
wsTotalWLANTspecsRejected.description: Total number of TSPECs rejected across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category.

wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted.name: wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted
wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted.description: Total number of TSPECs accepted from roaming clients across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category. The value of this object is also included in the wsTotalWLANTspecsAccepted object.

wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsRejected.name: wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsRejected
wsTotalWLANRoamingTspecsRejected.description: Total number of TSPECs rejected from roaming clients across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category. The value of this object is also included in the wsTotalWLANTspecsRejected object.

wsSwitchTspecStatusTable.name: wsSwitchTspecStatusTable
wsSwitchTspecStatusTable.description: This table contains TSPEC status parameters for peer controllers of the wireless controller.

wsSwitchTspecStatusEntry.name: wsSwitchTspecStatusEntry
wsSwitchTspecStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the TPEC status parameters for a specific peer of the wireless controller.

wsSwitchTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams.name: wsSwitchTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams
wsSwitchTspecTotalVoiceTrafficStreams.description: Total number of traffic streams currently established for the voice access category for the specified controller.

wsSwitchTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams.name: wsSwitchTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams
wsSwitchTspecTotalVideoTrafficStreams.description: Total number of traffic streams currently established for the video access category for the specified controller.

wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients.name: wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients
wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamClients.description: Total number of clients that currently possess one or more traffic streams in any access category for the specified controller.

wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingCl.name: wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingClients
wsSwitchTspecTotalTrafficStreamRoamingCl.description: Total number of roaming clients that currently possess one or more traffic streams in any access category for the specified controller.

wsSwitchTspecStatisticsTable.name: wsSwitchTspecStatisticsTable
wsSwitchTspecStatisticsTable.description: This table contains WLAN TSPEC statistics on a per access category (AC) basis for each controller in the peer group. Only the Cluster Controller maintains entries for peer controllers. A non-Cluster Controller controller just keeps its local statistics.

wsSwitchTspecStatisticsEntry.name: wsSwitchTspecStatisticsEntry
wsSwitchTspecStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry contains WLAN TSPEC statistics on a per access category (AC) basis for the specified wireless controller.

wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsRecvd.name: wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsRecvd
wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsTransmitted.name: wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsTransmitted
wsSwitchWLANTspecPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsSwitchWLANTspecBytesRecvd.name: wsSwitchWLANTspecBytesRecvd
wsSwitchWLANTspecBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received across all APs managed by this controller for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsSwitchWLANTspecBytesTransmitted.name: wsSwitchWLANTspecBytesTransmitted

wsSwitchWLANTspecsRejected.name: wsSwitchWLANTspecsRejected
wsSwitchWLANTspecsRejected.description: Total number of TSPECs rejected across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category.

wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted.name: wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted
wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsAccepted.description: Total number of TSPECs accepted from roaming clients across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category. This value of this object is also included in the wsSwitchWLANTspecsAccepted object.

wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsRejected.name: wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsRejected
wsSwitchWLANRoamingTspecsRejected.description: Total number of TSPECs rejected from roaming clients across all APs managed by this controller for the specified access category. The value of this object is also included in the wsSwitchWLANTspecsRejected object.

wsManagedAPTspecStatusTable.name: wsManagedAPTspecStatusTable
wsManagedAPTspecStatusTable.description: This table contains TSPEC status parameters for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPTspecStatusEntry.name: wsManagedAPTspecStatusEntry
wsManagedAPTspecStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC status parameters for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStreams.name: wsManagedAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStreams
wsManagedAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStreams.description: Indicates the current number of active traffic streams (TSs) for the specified access category of the WS managed AP.

wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClients.name: wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClients
wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClients.description: Indicates the current number of clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category of the WS managed AP.

wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoamingC.name: wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoamingClients
wsManagedAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoamingC.description: Indicates the current number of roaming clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category of the WS managed AP. The value of this object is also included in the wsManagedAPTspecNumTSClients object.

wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsTable.name: wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsTable
wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsTable.description: This table contains TSPEC statistics available for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsEntry.name: wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsEntry
wsManagedAPTspecStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC statistics for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPTspecPktsRecvd.name: wsManagedAPTspecPktsRecvd
wsManagedAPTspecPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received by this AP on the wireless network for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPTspecPktsTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPTspecPktsTransmitted
wsManagedAPTspecPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted by this AP on the wireless network for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPTspecBytesRecvd.name: wsManagedAPTspecBytesRecvd
wsManagedAPTspecBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received by this AP on the wireless network for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPTspecBytesTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPTspecBytesTransmitted
wsManagedAPTspecBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted by this AP on the wireless network for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPTspecsAccepted.name: wsManagedAPTspecsAccepted
wsManagedAPTspecsAccepted.description: Total number of TSPECs accepted by this AP on the wireless network for the specified access category.

wsManagedAPRoamingTspecsAccepted.name: wsManagedAPRoamingTspecsAccepted
wsManagedAPRoamingTspecsAccepted.description: Total number of TSPECs accepted from roaming clients by an AP on the wireless network for the specified access category. This value of this object is also included in the wsManagedAPTspecsAccepted object.

wsManagedAPRoamingTspecsRejected.name: wsManagedAPRoamingTspecsRejected
