wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusTable.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusTable
wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusTable.description: This table contains TSPEC status parameters per radio interface for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusEntry.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusEntry
wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC status parameters per radio interface for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecOperStatus.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecOperStatus
wsManagedAPRadioTspecOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operational status for the specified access category on this radio. If enabled(1), this access category operates in accordance with admission control mandatory (ACM) procedures.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumActiveTrafficStr.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumActiveTrafficStreams
wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumActiveTrafficStr.description: Indicates the current number of active traffic streams (TSs) for the specified access category on this radio.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamCli.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamClients
wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamCli.description: Indicates the current number of clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category on this radio.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamRoa.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamRoamingClients
wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTrafficStreamRoa.description: Indicates the current number of roaming clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category on this radio. The value of this object is also included in the wsManagedAPRadioTspecNumTSClients object.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeAdmitted.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeAdmitted
wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeAdmitted.description: Current sum of medium times allocated to clients with an active traffic stream (TS) belonging to the specified access category on this radio.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeUnallocat.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeUnallocated
wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeUnallocat.description: Amount of configured medium time not currently allocated for the specified access category on this radio that is available for both non-roaming and roaming clients.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeRoamingUn.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeRoamingUnallocated
wsManagedAPRadioTspecMediumTimeRoamingUn.description: Amount of configured medium time not currently allocated for the specified access category on this radio that is available for roaming clients only.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsTable.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsTable
wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsTable.description: This table contains TSPEC statistics available per radio interface for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsEntry.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsEntry
wsManagedAPRadioTspecStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC statistics per radio interface for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsRecvd.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsRecvd
wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received on this radio for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsTransmitted
wsManagedAPRadioTspecPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted on this radio for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesRecvd.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesRecvd
wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received on this radio for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesTransmitted
wsManagedAPRadioTspecBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted on this radio for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusTable.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusTable
wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusTable.description: This table contains TSPEC status parameters for each VAP on the specified radio interface for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusEntry.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusEntry
wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC status parameters for each VAP on the specified radio interface for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecOperStatus.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecOperStatus
wsManagedAPVAPTspecOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operational status for the specified access category on this VAP. If enabled(1), this access category operates in accordance with admission control mandatory (ACM) procedures.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStrea.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStreams
wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumActiveTrafficStrea.description: Indicates the current number of active traffic streams (TSs) for the specified access category on this VAP.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClien.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClients
wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamClien.description: Indicates the current number of clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category on this VAP.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoami.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoamingClients
wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTrafficStreamRoami.description: Indicates the current number of roaming clients with at least one active traffic stream (TS) for the specified access category on this VAP. The value of this object is also included in the wsManagedAPVAPTspecNumTSClients object.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeAdmitted.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeAdmitted
wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeAdmitted.description: Current sum of medium times allocated to clients with an active traffic stream (TS) belonging to the specified access category on this VAP.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeUnallocated.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeUnallocated
wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeUnallocated.description: Amount of configured medium time not currently allocated for the specified access category on this VAP that is available for both non-roaming and roaming clients.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeRoamingUnal.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeRoamingUnallocated
wsManagedAPVAPTspecMediumTimeRoamingUnal.description: Amount of configured medium time not currently allocated for the specified access category on this VAP that is available for roaming clients only.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsTable.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsTable
wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsTable.description: This table contains TSPEC statistics available for each VAP on the specified radio interface for all APs managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsEntry.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsEntry
wsManagedAPVAPTspecStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC statistics for each VAP on the specified radio for a specific AP managed by the controller.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsRecvd.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsRecvd
wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received on this VAP for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsTransmitted
wsManagedAPVAPTspecPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted on this VAP for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesRecvd.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesRecvd
wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received on this VAP for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesTransmitted.name: wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesTransmitted
wsManagedAPVAPTspecBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted on this VAP for all traffic streams belonging to the specified access category.

wsAssociatedClientTsStatusTable.name: wsAssociatedClientTsStatusTable
wsAssociatedClientTsStatusTable.description: This table contains TSPEC traffic stream status parameters for clients currently associated with managed APs. Only clients possessing one or more active traffic streams appear in this table.

wsAssociatedClientTsStatusEntry.name: wsAssociatedClientTsStatusEntry
wsAssociatedClientTsStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains TSPEC traffic stream status parameters for a specific client that is currently associated with the WS managed AP.

wsAssociatedClientTsTid.name: wsAssociatedClientTsTid
wsAssociatedClientTsTid.description: The traffic stream identifier (TID) indicated in the TSPEC that defines the traffic stream for the specified access category for the wireless client. Each traffic stream for a particular client must have a unique TID in the range 0-7, but per specification, any TID may map to any user priority and hence to any access category.

wsAssociatedClientTsAccessCategory.name: wsAssociatedClientTsAccessCategory
wsAssociatedClientTsAccessCategory.description: Access category (AC) of this client traffic stream. Only those ACs that support mandatory admission control are used. The currently supported AC values are: 0 - Voice 1 - Video

wsAssociatedClientTsDirection.name: wsAssociatedClientTsDirection
wsAssociatedClientTsDirection.description: The direction of the client traffic stream (TS) as indicated in the TSPEC. An uplink(1) TS monitors data traffic flowing from client station to AP, while a downlink(2) TS pertains to the opposite direction. A bidirectional(3) TS covers both directions and is treated as an uplink TS and downlink TS operating concurrently for the specified access category.

wsAssociatedClientTsUserPriority.name: wsAssociatedClientTsUserPriority
wsAssociatedClientTsUserPriority.description: The user priority indicated in the TSPEC that defines the traffic stream for the specified access category for the wireless client. QoS Data frames to/from the client containing this user priority are categorized as belonging to the traffic stream, depending on direction.

wsAssociatedClientTsMediumTime.name: wsAssociatedClientTsMediumTime
wsAssociatedClientTsMediumTime.description: Indicates the amount of time this client is allowed to access the wireless medium each second for the specified access category through this traffic stream. This value is calculated by the AP based on various parameters supplied in the TSPEC add request from the client. The medium time is specified as the number of 32 microsecond time units the client is allowed to access the wireless network each second. This is referred to as units of 32 usec-per-sec and is generally treated as an average value, with any over-usage in one interval deducted from the alotted medium time for the next interval.

wsAssociatedClientTsExcessUsageEvents.name: wsAssociatedClientTsExcessUsageEvents
wsAssociatedClientTsExcessUsageEvents.description: The number of times the wireless client has appreciably exceeded the medium time established for its TSPEC. The actual measure of 'appreciably exceeded' is implementation-dependent, but it is not necessarily a single occurrence of exceeding the medium time for any given one second interval. Rather, this event may be indicated after repeated violations of the medium time over some measurement interval, and is intended as an heuristic to identify a wireless client whose TSPEC medium time may be set too low relative to its actual traffic stream requirements. This object reflects the number of excess usage events that have accumulated, but have not been reported, through the Trap Manager, with such reporting enabled by the wsTspecTrapMode object. Whenever a trap report is generated for this event, the value of this object restarts counting from zero.

wsAssociatedClientTsRoamingClientIndicat.name: wsAssociatedClientTsRoamingClientIndicator
wsAssociatedClientTsRoamingClientIndicat.description: A flag indicating whether this traffic stream was established by a wireless client that was considered to be a roaming client.

wsAuthenticatedClientTunnelIpAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTunnelIpAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientTunnelIpAddress.description: Indicates network IP address of the client station, 0.0.0.0 indicates unknown. Tunnel IP subnet is present only for clients authenticated with tunneled VAPs.

wsAuthenticatedClientUserName.name: wsAuthenticatedClientUserName
wsAuthenticatedClientUserName.description: Indicates user name of the client that have authenticated via 802.1x, clients on networks with other security modes will not have a user name.

wsAuthenticatedClientSSID.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSSID
wsAuthenticatedClientSSID.description: Indicates the network on which the client is connected.

wsAuthenticatedClientVLAN.name: wsAuthenticatedClientVLAN
wsAuthenticatedClientVLAN.description: If client is on VAP using VLAN data forwarding mode, indicates current assigned VLAN.

wsAuthenticatedClientTxDataRate.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTxDataRate
wsAuthenticatedClientTxDataRate.description: Indicates the data rate, AP will actually support in setting up communications with client stations represented by a count from 2 - 1200, corresponding to data rates in multiples of 500 kbit/s from 1 Mbit/s to 600 Mbit/s. Supported Data Rate Mbps 2 1 4 2 11 5.5 12 6 18 9 and so on.

wsAuthenticatedClientInactivePeriod.name: wsAuthenticatedClientInactivePeriod
wsAuthenticatedClientInactivePeriod.description: For a current association, period of time that the AP has not seen any traffic for the client.

wsAuthenticatedClientDisassociateAction.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDisassociateAction
wsAuthenticatedClientDisassociateAction.description: This is an action object. Setting this object to start will initiate the disassociation of associated client. Read on this object will always return none.

wsAuthenticatedClientAge.name: wsAuthenticatedClientAge
wsAuthenticatedClientAge.description: Indicates time since the controller has received new data for this client.

wsAuthenticatedClientAssociatingSwitch.name: wsAuthenticatedClientAssociatingSwitch
wsAuthenticatedClientAssociatingSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the client is associated to an AP managed by this controller or peer-controller.

wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchMacAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchMacAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchMacAddress.description: MAC address of the WS associating the client.

wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIpAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIpAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIpAddress.description: IP address of the WS associating the client.

wsAuthenticatedClientDot11nCapable.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDot11nCapable
wsAuthenticatedClientDot11nCapable.description: Flag indicating whether this client is capable of 802.11n operation.

wsAuthenticatedClientStbcCapable.name: wsAuthenticatedClientStbcCapable
wsAuthenticatedClientStbcCapable.description: Flag indicating whether this client is capable of Space Time Block Code (STBC) operation.

wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelStatus.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelStatus
wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelStatus.description: Indicates whether L2 Distributed Tunneling is Enabled or Disabled

wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatu.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatus
wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelRoamStatu.description: Indicates whether the client is using the distrubuted tunnel or not. Also indicates if it is a roamed client or not.

wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac
wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelHomeAPMac.description: Indicates MAC Address of the client's Home AP. Here the client should be associated with the network on which the L2 Distributed Tunneling is enabled.

wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMa.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMac
wsAuthenticatedClientDistTunnelAssocAPMa.description: MAC Address of the client's Association AP to which the client has roamed to.

wsAuthenticatedClientAPMacAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientAPMacAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientAPMacAddress.description: MAC Address of the AP to which client is Authenticated.

wsAuthenticatedClientBSSID.name: wsAuthenticatedClientBSSID
wsAuthenticatedClientBSSID.description: BSSID of the VAP to which client is associated.

wsAuthenticatedClientRadioInterface.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRadioInterface
wsAuthenticatedClientRadioInterface.description: Indicates the radio interface on which client is associated.

wsAuthenticatedClientChannel.name: wsAuthenticatedClientChannel
wsAuthenticatedClientChannel.description: Indicates channel for associated client entry.

wsAuthenticatedClientNwTime.name: wsAuthenticatedClientNwTime
wsAuthenticatedClientNwTime.description: Indicates time since this client first authenticated with the network.

wsAuthenticatedClientIpAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientIpAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientIpAddress.description: Indicates network IPv4 address of the client station detetecd through ARP snooping, 0.0.0.0 indicates unknown.

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMSupported.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMSupported.description: Indicates if the Radio Resource Management (RRM) portion of the IEEE 802.11k standard is supported by client and RRM is enabled is on the AP Profile. Value 2 indicates the client supports RRM portion and RRM Mode is not enabled on AP Profile. Value 3 indicates client doesnot support RRM

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMLocationReportSu.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMLocationReportSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMLocationReportSu.description: Indicates if the client can support RRM location report requests.

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconTableMeasu.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconTableMeasurementSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconTableMeasu.description: Indicates if the client can detect APs via RRM beacon table reports.

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconActiveMeas.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconActiveMeasurementSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconActiveMeas.description: Indicates if the client supports active scan capability.

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMea.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMeasurementSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMBeaconPassiveMea.description: Indicates if the client supports passive scan capability.

wsAuthenticatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasu.name: wsAuthenticatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasurementSupported
wsAuthenticatedClientRRMChannelLoadMeasu.description: Indicates if the client supports RRM channel load measurement.

wsAuthenticatedClientDot11acCapable.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDot11acCapable
wsAuthenticatedClientDot11acCapable.description: Flag indicating whether this client is capable of 802.11ac operation.

wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsTable.name: wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsTable
wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsTable.description: This table contains statistics available for each client associated to a WS managed AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsEntry.name: wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsEntry
wsAuthenticatedClientStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain statistics available for each client associated a WS managed AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received by a managed AP from the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received by a managed AP from the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitted.name: wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitted.description: Total packets transmitted by a managed AP to the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitted.name: wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitted.description: Total bytes transmitted by a managed AP to the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientDuplicatePktsRecvd.description: Total duplicate packets received from the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsRecvd.description: Total fragmented packets received from the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsTrans.name: wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientFragmentedPktsTrans.description: Total fragmented packets transmitted to the client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryCount.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryCount
wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryCount.description: Indicates number of times transmits to client station succeeded after one or more retries.

wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryFailed.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryFailedCount
wsAuthenticatedClientTransmitRetryFailed.description: Number of times transmits to client station failed after one or more retries.

wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvDropped.name: wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientPktsRecvDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the receive direction by a managed AP from the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvDropped.name: wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientBytesRecvDropped.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction by a managed AP from the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitDropped.name: wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientPktsTransmitDropped.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction by a managed AP to the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitDroppe.name: wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientBytesTransmitDroppe.description: Total bytes dropped in the transmit direction by a managed AP to the client station. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsRecvd.description: Number of packets received by the AP from a client station that are in excess of the client's alotted traffic stream (TS) uplink bandwidth, or are for an access category requiring admission control to which the client station has not been admitted.

wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsTransm.name: wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientTsViolatePktsTransm.description: Number of packets transmitted by the AP to a client station that are in excess of the client's alotted traffic stream (TS) downlink bandwidth, or are for an access category requiring admission control to which the client station has not been admitted.

wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPSt.name: wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPStatusTable
wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPSt.description: This table is maintained to lookup all WS managed APs detected, client can see in its RF area.

wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPSt.name: wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPStatusEntry
wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborManagedAPSt.description: Each entry in this table contain WS managed APs that can be seen by client in its RF area.

wsAuthenticatedClientStationMacAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientStationMacAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientStationMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of a client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAP.name: wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAPMacAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAP.description: The Ethernet address of a WS managed AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAP.name: wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAPRadioInterface
wsAuthenticatedClientNeighborWSManagedAP.description: The radio interface of Managed AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientStationDiscoveryRea.name: wsAuthenticatedClientStationDiscoveryReason
wsAuthenticatedClientStationDiscoveryRea.description: Indicates the client status with respect to the Managed AP it is refering. One or more flags can be enabled at the same time.

wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.name: wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusTable
wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.description: This table is maintained to lookup clients associated to a specific VAP on a WS managed AP.

wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.name: wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry
wsVAPAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain clients associated to each VAP.

wsAuthenticatedVAPMacAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedVAPMacAddress
wsAuthenticatedVAPMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address assigned to a VAP to which the client is associated.

wsVAPAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.name: wsVAPAuthenticatedClientMacAddress
wsVAPAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of associated client station.

wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.name: wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusTable
wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.description: This table is maintained to lookup all clients associated to a particular network.

wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.name: wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry
wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain clients associated to a particular network.

wsAuthenticatedSSID.name: wsAuthenticatedSSID
wsAuthenticatedSSID.description: Indicates the network on which the client is connected.

wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.name: wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientMacAddress
wsSSIDAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.description: The Ethernet address of the client station.

wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.name: wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusTable
wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusTable.description: This table is maintained to lookup clients associated to the APs managed by the specific controller.

wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.name: wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry
wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contain client associated to each controller.

wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIPAddress.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIPAddress
wsAuthenticatedClientSwitchIPAddress.description: IP address of the WS associating the client.

wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.name: wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientMacAddress
wsSwitchAuthenticatedClientMacAddress.description: Ethernet address of the associated client station.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusTable.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusTable
wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusTable.description: This table contains client QoS status parameters of clients that are currently associated with managed APs. These objects represent the actual operational status values in effect for the clients.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusEntry.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusEntry
wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains client QoS status parameters for a client associated with the WS managed AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDo.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDown
wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitDo.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client, thus controlling the maximum receive rate from the AP for this wireless client. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). The displayed value represents the actual bandwidth rate in use for the client, which may differ from the configured value since the AP rounds down to the nearest 64000 bps. A value of 0 indicates bandwidth limiting is disabled in this direction for the client.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp
wsAuthenticatedClientQosBandwidthLimitUp.description: Maximum bandwidth rate allowed for the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP, thus controlling the maximum send rate from this wireless client to the AP. This parameter is specified in bits-per-second (bps). The displayed value represents the actual bandwidth rate in use for the client, which may differ from the configured value since the AP rounds down to the nearest 64000 bps. A value of 0 indicates bandwidth limiting is disabled in this direction for the client.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDow.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDownType
wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDow.description: Access list type used for the wireless down (outbound) direction from the AP to this client. The wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDownName object identifies the access list.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDow.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDownName
wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDow.description: Name of the access list in use in accordance with the wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlDownType as follows: none(1) - This object is not displayed. ip(2) - This specifies an IP access list number in the range 1-199, or an IP access list name as defined by the aclName object in the aclTable in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. mac(3) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid MAC access list name, as defined by the aclMacName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. ipv6(4) - This is an alphanumeric string from 1-31 characters, beginning with a letter. This must be a valid IPV6 access list name, as defined by the aclIpv6Name object in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. Note that numbered IP access lists are displayed here using a character string notation instead of an integer.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpT.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpType
wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpT.description: Access list type used for the wireless up (inbound) direction from this client to the AP. The wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpName object identifies the access list.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpN.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpName
wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpN.description: Name of the access list in use in accordance with the wsAuthenticatedClientQosAccessControlUpType as follows: none(1) - This object is not displayed. ip(2) - This specifies an IP access list number in the range 1-199, or an IP access list name as defined by the aclName object in the aclTable in the FASTPATH-QOS-ACL-MIB. Note that numbered IP access lists are displayed here using a character string notation instead of an integer.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDo.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType
wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDo.description: DiffServ policy type used for the wireless down (outbound) direction from the AP to this client. The wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName object identifies the DiffServ policy.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDo.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDownName
wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDo.description: Name of the DiffServ policy in use in accordance with the wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyDownType as follows: none(1) - This object is not displayed. in(2) - This specifies a DiffServ policy name, as defined by the agentDiffServPolicyName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-DIFFSERV-PRIVATE-MIB. Note that only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUp.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType
wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUp.description: DiffServ policy type used for the wireless up (inbound) direction from this client to the AP. The wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName object identifies the DiffServ policy.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUp.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUpName
wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUp.description: Name of the DiffServ policy in use in accordance with the wsAuthenticatedClientQosDiffservPolicyUpType as follows: none(1) - This object is not displayed. in(2) - This specifies a DiffServ policy name, as defined by the agentDiffServPolicyName object in the FASTPATH-QOS-DIFFSERV-PRIVATE-MIB. Note that only DiffServ policy defintions of type 'in' are supported for wireless client QoS operation.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosOperStatus.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosOperStatus
wsAuthenticatedClientQosOperStatus.description: Designates the AP quality-of-service operational status for this wireless client. This represents the combined states of the wsApClientQosMode object and the wsNetworkClientQosMode object for the wireless network to which this client is associated.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsTa.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsTable
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsTa.description: This table contains statistics available for each client associated to a WS managed AP, but accumulated for the duration of the entire WLAN session, inclusive of client roaming.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsEn.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsEntry
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionStatisticsEn.description: Each entry in this table contain statistics available for each client associated a WS managed AP, but accumulated for the duration of the entire WLAN session, inclusive of client roaming.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvd.description: Total packets received by managed APs from the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvd.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvd.description: Total bytes received by managed APs from the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmit.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmit.description: Total packets transmitted by managed APs to the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesTransmi.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesTransmi.description: Total bytes transmitted by managed APs to the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionDuplicatePkt.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionDuplicatePktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionDuplicatePkt.description: Total duplicate packets received from the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPk.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPk.description: Total fragmented packets received from the client station. throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPk.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPktsTransmitted
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionFragmentedPk.description: Total fragmented packets transmitted to the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetr.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetryCount
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetr.description: Indicates number of times transmits to client station succeeded after one or more retries throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetr.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetryFailedCount
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTransmitRetr.description: Number of times transmits to client station failed after one or more retries throughout the duration of the current WLAN session.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvDrop.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsRecvDrop.description: Total packets dropped in the receive direction by managed APs from the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvDro.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesRecvDro.description: Total bytes dropped in the receive direction by managed APs from the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless up (inbound) direction from client to AP.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmit.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmitDropped
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionPktsTransmit.description: Total packets dropped in the transmit direction by managed APs to the client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session. This is due to client QoS actions affecting the wireless down (outbound) direction from AP to client.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesTransmi.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionBytesTransmitDropped

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTSViolatePkt.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsRecvd
wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTSViolatePkt.description: Number of packets received by managed APs from a client station throughout the duration of the current WLAN session that are in excess of the client's alotted traffic stream (TS) uplink bandwidth, or are for an access category requiring admission control to which the client station has not been admitted.

wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTSViolatePkt.name: wsAuthenticatedClientSessionTSViolatePktsTransmitted

wsAuthenticatedClientQosCachedStatusTabl.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosCachedStatusTable
wsAuthenticatedClientQosCachedStatusTabl.description: This table contains cached client QoS status parameters of clients that are currently associated with managed APs. These objects represent values that were retrieved from a RADIUS server for this client. See the wsAuthenticatedClientQosStatusTable for the current set of operational values in use for this client.

wsAuthenticatedClientQosCachedStatusEntr.name: wsAuthenticatedClientQosCachedStatusEntry
